(196, 'Everyday Organic Duck Eggs - Box of 6 Eggs', '3.00', 'Everyday Organic Duck Eggs - Box of 6 Eggs\r\nEggs are fragrant, fatty, with rich yellow yolks, safe for young children. Eggs are taken from flocks of free-range ducks in extremely free and comfortable conditions. Running in the morning and playing in the large garden, taking shelter in the cool barn at noon, sleeping on a bamboo pole at night. All food is certified organic in addition to corn. In addition, added green vegetables, soy protein, fish protein, vitamins... absolutely no antibiotics, growth hormones, egg-laying stimulants....', 2, 'img193.png', 100),
(197, 'More Green Mussels Shell Organic Newzealand 1kg', '17.00', 'New Zealand green mussel: firm, chewy, sweet, aromatic and greasy mussel meat. Mussels have a lot of meat, so the problem of products shrinking when processing is certified organic New Zealand\r\n- New Zealand green mussels are rich in nutrients, high in iron, protein and essential Omega-3 fatty acids; In addition to being very low in fat, calories and cholesterol. Green mussels are very good for the elderly to improve bone and joint problems. After being caught and harvested according to strict standards, mussels are put into a line of shelling, steaming and freezing immediately so they can keep their fresh meat.\r\n- New Zealand green mussels, because they have been steamed, have a lot of meat themselves, so they can limit the problem of atrophy when processing, ensuring that the product will be very beautiful when processed and can be enjoyed.\r\nNew Zealand green mussels are a famous specialty in New Zealand waters, unlike other green mussels, New Zealand green mussels are grown according to clean standards from seed to harvest. The farming process strictly controls everything including food, environment, living conditions, care regimen.\r\nDelicious dishes from New Zealand Pure Organic green mussels such as: steamed lemongrass, Thai steamed, grilled with onion fat, baked in cheese, fried with vermicelli, fried with spaghetti, cooked in hot pot,\r\n\r\nCharacteristic:\r\n- New Zealand Organic Certification', 2, 'img194.png', 100),
(198, 'Whole Siamese Duck - 1kg (Pre-order)', '7.00', 'Give me a duck, and I\'ll show you how to become… an emperor on the dinner table.” Based on the records in ancient medical records and the thousand-year-old eating habits of the Eastern people, the attraction and The nutritional value of duck dishes is self-evident.', 2, 'img195.png', 100),
(199, 'Baking Soda (Baking Salt) Radiant Whole Foods 500g', '2.00', 'Origin: USA Packing: 500g Edible Used for cooking, home care...\r\nOrigin: USA\r\nPacking: 500g\r\nEdible\r\nIngredients: Sodium Bicarbonate.\r\nUser Manual:\r\n- Create a spongy structure for cakes: Add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda and mix with 100g of baking powder.\r\n- Increase the crispness of fried and fried foods: add a little baking soda to the fried dough.\r\n- Save time and cooking fuel: add 1/3 teaspoon of baking soda to the pot to help simmer, stew, and sweet dishes quickly soften.\r\nWash vegetables and fruits: a mixture of baking soda, water, and lemon helps to clean vegetables effectively.\r\n- Dental care: mix baking soda with water, salt, essential oils, form a paste to brush teeth to help clean, whiten teeth, de-blind Do not use more than 3-4 times/month.\r\nExfoliate: Mix 3 parts baking soda with 1 part water and use this mixture to exfoliate your face and body.\r\n- Remove acne: mix 1 tablespoon of baking soda with a small bowl of water, soak the acne skin in this mixture 2 times a day, the condition of acne will improve after a few days.\r\n- Relaxing soak: mix 3 tablespoons of baking soda into a basin of water to soak your feet. Baking soda combined with apple cider vinegar to soak in the bath also gives you moments of relaxation like at a spa. Cleaning the bathtub again is an added value of this mixture.\r\n- Clean the scalp: mix 1 teaspoon of baking soda with shampoo and wash as usual, the hair will be cleaner and smoother, but should not be used more than 2 times / month.\r\nBody Deodorant: Brush some dry baking soda or a mixture of baking soda and water into your armpits.\r\n- Soothe insect bites: apply some dry baking soda or a mixture of baking soda mixed with water to the insect bite.\r\n- Hand sanitizer: mix 3 parts baking soda with 1 part water and use this mixture to replace hand sanitizer, remove bacteria and stains.\r\nSunburn remedy: soak in a warm bath with 1/2 cup of baking soda.\r\n- Improve exercise efficiency: mix half a teaspoon of baking soda with 250ml of water, drink 1 hour before exercise, do not use more than 1-2 times a week.\r\n- Improve heartburn, indigestion and ulcer pain: mix 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda with half a glass of water, drink every 2 hours, note not to drink more than 7 times / day or 3 times / day if you are over 60 age.\r\n- Multi-purpose cleaner: use a mixture of baking soda, water or apple cider vinegar to clean household items, kitchen, bathroom.\r\n- Deodorize, purify the air: place a cup of baking soda in the refrigerator to eliminate odors, or add 1/3 cup of baking soda about 10 drops of your favorite essential oils to purify the air in the room.\r\nStorage: Store in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight.', 3, 'img196.png', 100),
(200, 'Bich Chi organic white noodle soup 200g', '2.00', 'Bich Chi organic white noodle soup\r\nCertified Organic Europe, USDA\r\nNet weight: 200g Hsd: 8/2021\r\n100% organic rice ingredients, no preservatives are used.\r\nHow to use: wash with clean water, put rice noodles in a pot of boiling water for 6-8 minutes, take out and rinse with clean water.\r\nUse stir-fry, eat broth as you like.', 3, 'img197.png', 100),
(201, 'Organic baby millet biscuits Sottolestelle 250G', '6.00', 'The best recipes are for kids who respect their health, so that they get used to less sweet flavors at an early age. The cookies come in a variety of flavors and are delicious, free of refined sugar and sweetened with rice syrup and apple juice. Obtained with Senatore Cappelli Premium Wheat Flour and extra virgin olive oil. No milk and eggs. For an organic product provides and educates the youngest people on a healthy and authentic diet so that they become conscious adults.', 3, 'img198.png', 100),
(202, 'Organic baby carrot apple biscuit sottolestelle 300G', '6.00', 'The best recipes are for kids who respect their health, so that they get used to less sweet flavors at an early age. The cookies come in a variety of flavors and are delicious, with no refined sugar and sweetened with rice syrup and apple juice. Obtained with Senatore Cappelli premium wheat flour and extra virgin olive oil. No milk and eggs. For an organic product, provide and educate the youngest people about a healthy and authentic diet so that they become conscious adults.', 3, 'img199.png', 100),
(203, 'Luce Organic Sweet Corn 340g', '4.00', 'Canned Organic Sweet Corn LUCE\r\nSweet corn is an old grain that appeared in Mexico more than 9,000 years ago. Its high nutritional value explains its popularity around the world, which is also the reason why it has become one of the popular crops worldwide.\r\nIngredients: Organic Sweet Corn, Water, Sea Salt\r\nInstructions for use: Serve cold with tomatoes, avocado, fish. Serve hot, stir with 2.3 tablespoons of butter to serve with meats\r\nStorage: Store in a cool, dry place and avoid direct sunlight\r\nOnce opened, keep refrigerated, sealed in a glass or plastic container and use within 3 to 4 days.\r\n\r\nContains no additives, colorants, radioactive or ionizing agents\r\nContains no allergens.\r\nNote: Once opened, refrigerate in a glass or plastic container and use within 3 to 4 days.\r\nOrigin: Italy.\r\nCertified organic AB (Agriculture Biologique) and EU', 3, 'img200.png', 100),
(204, 'Organic sottolestelle bread flour - 125g', '5.00', 'Wheatgrass is high in fiber, low in calories, and packed with vitamins and minerals.\r\n\r\nBurnt wheat is an especially good source of manganese, selenium, phosphorus and magnesium.\r\n\r\nWheatgrass also contains lignans, which are phytochemicals thought to have protective effects against breast and prostate cancer.\r\n\r\nBurnt wheat is spongy, enhancing their nutritional value and making them easier to digest.\r\n\r\nWith delicious, attractive flavors will enrich your daily breakfast.\r\n\r\nWheat is crispy, lightly sweet, with the whole germ intact, so the nutritional content is complete.\r\n\r\nUser object:\r\n\r\nEat directly as a snack, or mix with milk, chia seeds, or dried seeds and eat as a delicious breakfast or snack.\r\n\r\nPregnant women, nursing mothers and infants over 1 year old can use it.\r\n\r\nSuitable as snacks for young children, office workers or you are on a weight loss diet.\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% organic wheat pops\r\n\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle - Italy\r\nExpiry date: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan\r\nNot genetically modified', 3, 'img201.png', 100),
(205, 'Markal Organic Corn Flour - 500g', '6.00', 'Ingredients: 100% Organic Corn.\r\nNutrition Facts: Cornmeal is naturally gluten-free, suitable for people who want to limit the gluten content of their diets.\r\n\r\nDirections for use: Can be used alone or mixed with plain flour. Cornstarch is incorporated into traditional flour to make breads, cakes, pancakes, and muffins. Cornstarch can also be used as a binder in sauces and creams and a thickener in soups. When using only powder\r\nCorn will create delicious corn cakes (corn cakes, cookies...).\r\nStorage Instructions: Store in a cool, dry place, away from direct light.\r\nOrigin: Italy\r\n\r\nCertified organic AB and EU', 3, 'img202.png', 100),
(206, 'Probios Organic Fried Rice Flour 375g', '6.00', 'Origin: ProBios – Italy\r\n\r\nShelf Life : 12 months from the date of manufacture\r\n\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\n\r\nVegan\r\n\r\nNon-GMO\r\n\r\nGluten Free\r\n\r\nIngredients: 98% corn flour, salt\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe organic breadcrumbs are completely gluten-free.\r\n\r\nOrganic breadcrumbs absorb 50% less oil than conventional flour-based breadcrumbs.\r\n\r\nCorn flakes are a healthy alternative to recipes that are lighter, easier to digest, and are perfect for people with gluten intolerance.\r\n\r\nThis is a sauce made from organic ingredients from Italy\r\n\r\nUser manual :\r\n\r\nUsed to create porosity, puffiness and crispiness in food recipes.', 3, 'img203.png', 100),
(207, 'Organic Rice Flour 500gr', '4.00', 'USDA Certification\r\n\r\nCertification EU ORGANIC BIO LOGO (EU) organic production process and organic farming method\r\n\r\nLotus Floating organic powder with ingredients of 100% rice is grown, harvested and milled into powder according to organic standards. Jasmine rice flour (jasmine rice) is used to make cakes such as rice paper, rolls, rice cakes, cakes, pancakes, banhha soup, spring rolls,... Or make vermicelli and pho. ... Rice flour can also be used to cook baby food.', 3, 'img204.png', 100),
(208, 'GERMANY MULTI-PURPOSE 405 Bauckhof 1kg', '5.00', 'Bauckhof Organic All-Purpose Flour is the right choice for the whole family\'s kitchen. The product has 10% protein, suitable for making cakes, dumplings, cookies. In addition, if using flour to make moon cakes, bread will also be very good. Wheat flour is packed in environmentally friendly paper bags. Products are imported in full package from Germany to Vietnam by BGroup Joint Stock Company.\r\n\r\nElement:\r\n\r\n- Flour.\r\n\r\n- From organic farming.\r\n\r\n- Demeter organic certification.\r\n\r\nUses:\r\n\r\n- Ideal for breads, rolls, cookies, pizza, etc.\r\n\r\n- Use in combination to prepare delicious and attractive dishes.\r\n\r\n- Use to beautify such as restoring skin cells, rejuvenating skin, ...\r\n\r\nUsing:\r\n\r\n- Mix flour with ingredients to make cakes or prepare dishes, helping you get a perfect dish.\r\n\r\n- Store the product in a cool, dry place.', 3, 'img205.png', 100),
(209, 'Organic Whole Wheat Flour T150 Markal 1kg', '6.00', 'Element :\r\n100% organic whole wheat flour T150\r\nCharacteristics :\r\n- Whole wheat flour is milled from brown wheat kernels with the bran, fiber and germ, not refined. As a result, nutrients such as vitamins, proteins and additional fats are optimally preserved. When making bread with whole wheat flour, the cake will be less puffy, heavy in texture and not as smooth as when using white flour. Unlike white flour, whole wheat flour contains all parts of the wheat kernel: the endosperm or endosperm (starch), bran husk, fiber, and germ (which contains additional proteins and fats). ). Can be combined with a little white flour to increase the puffiness of the cake.\r\nWhy use organic whole wheat flour:\r\n- Low glycemic index, suitable and limit the risk of diabetes.\r\nNutritional content is higher than white flour.\r\nDue to the dense and heavy texture of the cake, you will be fuller for longer, limit snacking and gain weight.\r\n- Stronger and more delicious taste. No GMOs, No Chemical Pesticides, No Preservatives. Store in a cool, dry place away from sources of heat and moisture. Products imported directly from France.\r\nCertified organic AB (Agriculture Biologique) and EU', 3, 'img206.png', 100),
(210, 'Organic All-Purpose White Wheat Flour T55 Markal 1kg', '6.00', 'Ingredients: 100% organic wheat flour T55\r\nCharacteristics :\r\n- Soft, white, light texture.\r\n- Creates more porosity and puffiness than whole wheat flour.\r\n- Use in recipes for bread and cakes. Can be mixed with organic whole wheat flour. No GMOs, No Chemical Pesticides, No Preservatives. Store in a cool, dry place, away from moisture and high temperature. Products imported directly from France. Certified organic AB (Agriculture Biologique) and EU', 3, 'img207.png', 100),
(211, 'Ubon Organic Tapioca Powder 400g', '3.00', 'Origin: Thailand Certified organic Europe, USA, Japan, Korea, Thailand Packing: 400g\r\nTapioca starch, also known as tapioca flour, Dao flour (Northern Vietnamese dialect), filtered flour (Central Vietnamese dialect), is the starch of the tapioca root (cassava). In the world, tapioca starch is often used as an additive in the preparation of sauces. In Vietnam, tapioca starch is also an auxiliary ingredient to create consistency for tea dishes and some cakes such as pork skin cake, filter cake. In the South, tapioca starch is flour obtained from tapioca tubers, a lowland tuber in Kien Giang, An Giang, Hau Giang, and Dong Thap Muoi, and tapioca starch is called refined wheat flour.\r\n\r\nUse in a variety of dishes:\r\n- Combine with flours in cake and dessert recipes\r\n- As a binder, thickener in soup recipes, sauces\r\n\r\n\r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from high heat and moisture.', 3, 'img208.png', 100),
(212, 'Organic Vegetable Seasoning Powder Sottolestelle 100g', '4.00', 'Seasoning powder in the form of easy-to-dissolve tablets, shortens the time of stewing vegetables and fruits as usual while still giving the broth natural color and natural aroma like a well-cooked stew.\r\n\r\nVegetable seasoning powder with Sottolestelle\'s drying technology and unique processing secret helps preserve fiber and minerals in each ingredient, not only safe and natural, but also helps your family\'s meals more peaceful, full of flavor.\r\n\r\nSalient features of Sottolestelle Organic Vegetable Seasoning Powder:\r\n\r\n- No MSG, no additives\r\n\r\n- No added preservatives and artificial colors\r\n\r\n- The ingredients are completely natural\r\n\r\nOrganic seasoning powder is suitable for vegetarians, dieters, eatclean, macrobiotics, etc., especially suitable for babies in the weaning period.\r\n\r\nIngredients: Salt, brown sugar, vegetable powder 13.3% (onion, celery, carrot, tomato, spinach, parsley), corn starch, sunflower oil, yeast extract, turmeric powder first%\r\n\r\nUser manual:\r\n\r\n- Used to make soup, soup, delicious natural hot pot without boiling vegetables\r\n\r\n– Use seasoning, tasting, marinating, stir-frying, and seasoning for dishes, whether vegetarian or non-vegetarian, to help meat dishes have more digestive nutrients.\r\n\r\nStorage: Fully sealed when using, keep in a cool, dry place.\r\n\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nShelf Life: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan\r\nNon-GMO', 3, 'IMG209.png', 100),
(213, 'Meister Backpulver Biovegan Organic Baking Powder - 17g', '2.00', 'Ingredients: corn starch, acidity regulator: monopotassium tartate (24.7% pure wine), baking soda (NaHCO3) Biovegan organic baking powder to help create a spongy structure for cakes such as cupcakes, muffins , cookies, rolls…\r\n \r\nIngredients: Organic tapioca starch, sodium carbonate, potassium tartrate (22.8%), organic lemon juice powder, thickener: organic guar gum.\r\n- Instructions for use: 17g bag used for 500g powder. Suitable for recipes for cakes, pies, cookies...\r\nStorage Instructions: Store in a cool, dry place. Avoid sources of heat and moisture.\r\nOrigin: Germany EU organic certification.', 3, 'img210.png', 100),
(214, 'Organic Agar Agar Biovegan Powder 30g', '5.00', 'Ingredients: 100% organic agar agar powder.\r\n\r\nInstructions for use: 1 full teaspoon (3.5g) is equivalent to 6 gelatin leaves, used for 500ml of liquid. The dose can be adjusted depending on the desired level\r\n+ How to make hot products: Mix 3.5 agar agar powder in 100ml of liquid until the powder is completely dissolved. Pour the mixture into the remaining liquid and stir well while simmering over low heat for 2 minutes. Then put the mixture in the refrigerator for about 3 hours.\r\n+ How to make cold finished product: Mix 3.5 agar agar powder in 100ml of liquid until the powder is completely dissolved. Then stir well and simmer for 1 minute. Turn off the heat and let the mixture cool, then add the other ingredients. Place the mixture in the refrigerator for 3 hours.\r\n\r\nNote: Because the packaging is degradable, the contents can easily stick together. This does not affect the quality or taste of the product\r\nStorage Instructions: Store in a cool, dry place. Avoid sources of heat and moisture.\r\nOrigin: Germany\r\n\r\nEU organic certification.', 3, 'img211.png', 100),
(215, 'Arrowhead Mill Organic Gluten-Free Tapioca Flour 510G', '6.00', 'Ingredients: 100% USDA Certified Organic Tapioca Flour Directions for Use: Use in baking, as a food additive or as a beverage. Storage: Store in a cool, dry place Shelf life: 1 year from the date of production This Tapioca flour has long been famous as a drink with cool taste and body heat, extremely popular in every household. family every summer. In addition, women are also more interested in pure tapioca flour because they have the ability to effectively treat acne, remove freckles and aid in exfoliating your skin.\r\n8 unexpected effects of cassava\r\n- Used to treat colds, fevers, boils, headaches and prevent heat rash\r\n- Used to treat sunstroke, headache, thirst, hot fever, sweating, hot stomach, vomiting\r\n- Used to treat symptoms of hot chest and abdomen\r\n- Used to treat bloody stools, food poisoning\r\n- Used to treat acute laryngitis, pharyngitis\r\n- Used to treat wounds that bleed a lot\r\n- Treat acne, drink a lot of alcohol and have bloody stools, or boils.\r\n- Alcohol poisoning', 3, 'img212.png', 100),
(216, 'Bich Chi organic brown rice vermicelli, box 200g', '3.00', 'Rice vermicelli with small, round, brown fibers is made from safe and quality pure organic brown rice. Bich Chi organic brown rice vermicelli in a convenient 200g box, just boiled through boiling water, you can use and process your favorite dishes such as stir-fry, mix,... Bich Chi dry noodles are convenient and quick for you. quick meal and b...\r\n\r\nProduct Type\r\nOrganic brown rice vermicelli\r\n\r\nWeight\r\n200g\r\n\r\nType of yarn\r\nRound, small, brown yarn\r\n\r\nElement\r\n100% organic brown rice. No preservatives are used\r\n\r\nHow to use\r\nSoak vermicelli in cold water for about 5-10 minutes. Cook in boiling water for about 4-6 minutes, take out and rinse with clean water, use whatever you want. Body fried with shrimp, crab, meat, eggs, vegetables, spices..., cooked with broth, chicken, duck, pork... or used with hot pot or used as fresh vermicelli.\r\n\r\nPreserve\r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight and high temperatures\r\n\r\nTrademark\r\nBich Chi (Vietnam)\r\n\r\nMade in\r\nVietnam\r\n\r\nRice vermicelli, also known as dry rice vermicelli, is made from plain rice, after being washed, soaked and softened, it is ground to a fine powder, then thinly coated, then cut into fibers and dried in the sun.\r\n\r\nThe advantage of rice vermicelli is that it can be preserved for a long time without fear of mold and spoilage and rice vermicelli can be processed into many simple and delicious dishes.', 3, 'img213.png', 100),
(217, 'Markal Organic Black Beans 500g', '6.00', 'Characteristics:\r\n- Rich in protein: helps maintain weight and health, strengthens muscles, supports weight loss.\r\n- Rich in fiber, supporting effective body purification.\r\nRich in protein, vitamins A, E, B, fiber, essential amino acids and minerals, helps nourish the skin from the inside out, improving the smoothness of the skin.\r\n- Contains anthocyanin polyphenols: active antioxidants, anti-aging, reducing the risk of arteriosclerosis, cholesterol and promoting lipid metabolism.\r\n- According to Oriental Medicine, black beans have the effect of tonic blood, tonic kidney, normalize the activity of stomach, spleen... Ingredients: 100% organic black beans.\r\nUser Manual:\r\nSoak for 12 hours. Then let dry. Cook beans in boiling water with a little salt added for about 1 hour. Serve hot with rice or meat or cold as a salad with sauce. It is a typical dish of South Americans (fejioada, burritos and enchiladas...) Vietnamese food: cooked with tea, porridge, soup, milled.', 3, 'img214.png', 100),
(218, 'Markal Organic Azuki Red Beans 500g', '5.00', 'Azuki red beans, also known as small bean chains, contain an abundant amount of protein: help maintain weight and health, strengthen muscles, support weight loss....\r\n- Rich in fiber: supports digestion, strengthens resistance.\r\n- Contains vitamins of group B and has alkaline properties: laxative, intestinal, detoxifies the intestines and liver very effectively.\r\n- Ingredients in skin care mask recipes.\r\n- Is the dominant flavor in most Japanese sweets\r\n \r\nIngredients: 100% organic azuki red beans.\r\n \r\nInstructions for use: Soak for 12 hours. Then let dry. Cook the beans in boiling water with a little salt for about 45 minutes in a ratio of 1 amount of beans to 3 amounts of water. Serve hot with rice or meat or cold as a salad with sauce. Vietnamese food: cook tea, porridge, soup, grind into powder...\r\n \r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from high heat and moisture. Better stored in glass jars. Products imported directly from France.\r\nCertified organic organic Agriculture Biologique and EU', 3, 'img215.png', 100),
(219, 'Cocovie Organic Cooking Coconut Oil 450ml', '5.00', 'Special Features of Cocovie\'s Cooking Coconut Oil\r\n\r\nRich in Lauric Acid: supports the digestive process, creating a feeling of lightness\r\nHigh smoke point: makes food safe when frying at high temperatures\r\nUnrefined: protect health, reduce cancer risk', 3, 'img216.png', 100),
(220, 'Cocovie Organic Premium Coconut Oil 260ml', '7.00', 'Premium coconut oil - keep your belly beautiful thanks to fat - with 100% organic coconut extract, rich in lauric acid, which converts to energy quickly without accumulating fat like other fats.\r\n\r\nIngredients: Ingredients: 100% organic coconut\r\n\r\nHow to use\r\n\r\nTake 1-2 teaspoons before each meal\r\nUsed to mix vegetables, salads\r\nDirectly add to tea, coffee, milk, juice and other popular drinks, both nutritious and flavorful.', 3, 'img217.png', 100),
(221, 'Bragg Organic Cold Pressed Extra Virgin Olive Oil 473ml', '17.00', 'Extra Virgin Olive Oil Bragg: USDA Organic Certified Organic Premium oil first pressed, acidity 0.51% (world standard =<0.8% ) Unrefined, unfiltered Rich in unrefined short-chain fats heart-healthy saturation and antioxidants Meets and exceeds the standards of Olive Oil published by The International Olive Oil Council\'s (IOOC) for quality and purity beautiful over the centuries\r\nFor fresh produce, the actual weight may vary by about 10%.\r\n\r\nHow to use:\r\n\r\nPerfect for mixing salads, pastas, vegetables, sauces, vinegars, even popcorn. You can also deep fry this Extra Virgin Olive Oil.\r\n\r\nPreserve:\r\n\r\nShould be stored in a cool, dry place, protected from sunlight.\r\n\r\nFor more information about Extra Virgin Olive Oil (EVOO) Bragg:\r\n\r\n- Extra Virgin is only the first pressed oil to bring out the best quality with the most nutrients. For Olive oil in general, there will be other types like Virgin/Pure/Pomance, only later pressings make the quality of the oil worse.\r\n\r\n- Cold pressing is a method of pressing oil that is not affected by oxidation by temperature.\r\n\r\n- Organic refers to the method of growing olives that are not contaminated by GMOs and chemicals.\r\n\r\n- Color: EVOO will have a darker color than other lines of Olive oil, EVOO Bragg has a very beautiful golden brown color.\r\n\r\n- Taste: Taste is also a qualitative factor in determining whether olive oil is genuine or not. For high quality oils you can smell the fresh olives.\r\n\r\n- The free acid index is an important indicator to evaluate the quality of olive oil. For the EVOO series according to the international standard of IOOC it is less than 0.8%, but for the EVOO Bragg it is 0.51% lower than the general standard. The reason olive oil is better, the lower this number is because the oil is actually an ester of a fatty acid. In the process of pressing under the effects of oxidizing oil, the bonds will be broken to create free acids. Thus, the free acid reflects the oxidizing effect of the cooking oil. The higher this number, the more oxidized the oil is and the stronger the odor becomes.\r\n\r\nBy determining this index will determine the quality of EVOO, it is also an important parameter for people to be able to determine how fake EVOO oil is. In fact, there are many fake EVOOs on the market today.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe peroxide ratio determines the initial oxidation of an oil. Peroxidation is oxidation. Exposure to heat, light, and metal surfaces accelerates oil oxidation.\r\n\r\nThe lower this value, the longer the oil will retain its shelf life and will delay the possibility of going rancid, while a high peroxide value usually indicates poor handling and low quality of the oil. Thus Olive Oil has a low peroxide value which means it is more stable and if stored properly, the shelf life is extended.\r\nEVOO Bragg has a peroxide value of 10.8 meqO2/kg, while the standard IOOC is <= 20 meqO2/kg', 3, 'img218.png', 100),
(222, 'Markal Organic Chickpeas 500g', '7.00', 'ELEMENT\r\n100% organic chickpeas\r\nUSES\r\nChickpeas provide many vitamins and minerals such as fiber, protein, folic acid, iron, copper, zinc and magnesium.\r\n- Reduce the risk of certain diseases such as heart disease, obesity, diabetes and maintain a healthy health.\r\n- As a vegetable protein dish, it can be used in the diet to lose weight.\r\nUSING\r\n- Wash beans and soak beans in clean water for about 8 hours (or overnight) before processing. Used to cook with rice, porridge, soup, make sauce. Put in a pressure cooker to cook beans faster. - Roasted to use in salads, yogurt, mixed with breakfast cereals, mixed with mayonnaise. After roasting, it can be pureed to make bread, baking, cakes and muffins. - Can also be used as raw materials for making baby food from 4 months old.\r\nHOW TO STORAGE Store in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight', 3, 'img219.png', 100),
(223, 'Markal Organic Peas - 500g', '6.00', 'Ingredients: 100% shelled and split green and yellow peas.\r\nCharacteristics :\r\n- rich in vitamins B1, B5, B9, protein, potassium, iron, magnesium, zinc, calcium, .. is a nutritional alternative from meat and milk, suitable for vegetarian diets.\r\n- Rich in insoluble fiber: helps improve intestinal digestion. Peas are also considered one of the effective foods against stomach cancer.\r\n- Suitable for diabetics: a test showed that a person after digesting 36g of glucide in peas had a glycemic index 1/3 of that obtained after eating the same amount of glucide in potato.\r\nUsage instructions: wash the beans. Fill the pot with water. Add the beans and cook over low heat for 1 hour until the beans are soft. Used to cook porridge, soup, salad...\r\nPreserved in dry, cool place. Better stored in glass jars.\r\nProducts imported directly from France.\r\nAgriculture Biologique & EU organic certification', 3, 'img220.png', 100),
(224, 'IL Nutrimento Organic Cold Pressed Hemp Seed Oil 250ml', '11.00', 'Origin: Italy\r\n\r\nEU organic certification\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% cold pressed hemp seed oil\r\n\r\nIl Nutrimento Organic Hemp Seed Oil is obtained without preheating the seeds or presses prior to pressing and without the need for additional heat during extraction. It is rich in polyunsaturated fats and naturally rich in omega-3 fatty acids. Replacing saturated fats with unsaturated fats in the diet contributes to the maintenance of normal blood cholesterol levels. A varied and balanced diet and healthy lifestyle should be followed.\r\n\r\nUsage: Use directly in dishes, do not cook\r\n\r\nStorage: In the refrigerator after opening', 3, 'img221.png', 100),
(225, 'Naturgreen Organic Flaxseed Oil 250ml', '8.00', 'Flaxseed oil is different from other vegetable oils thanks to its very high content of omega 3, namely ALA (alpha-linoleic acid) and omega 9 (oleic acid) polyunsaturated fatty acids. In addition, flaxseed oil is also considered as the vegetable oil with the best ratio of omega 6 / omega 3. As an alternative source of fish food, which contains a lot of omega 3. Suitable for vegetarian diets.\r\nFor fresh produce, the actual weight may vary by about 10%.\r\n\r\nFlaxseed oil is different from other vegetable oils thanks to its very high content of omega 3, namely ALA (alpha-linoleic acid) and omega 9 (oleic acid) polyunsaturated fatty acids. In addition, flaxseed oil is also considered as the vegetable oil with the best ratio of omega 6 / omega 3.\r\n\r\nAs an alternative source of fish food, which contains a lot of omega 3. Suitable for vegetarian diets.\r\n\r\nWhy is omega 3 good for the body?\r\n\r\nOmega 3 is one of the components that make up the mucous membranes that make up the cells in the body and helps the cells in their genetic activity.\r\n\r\n- When absorbed by the body, ALA (alpha-linoleic) is converted into DHA (docosahexaenoic acid) and EPA (Eicosapentaenoic acid) to help improve type 2 diabetes.\r\n\r\nDHA is an indispensable ingredient for eye and nervous system development. DHA deficiency may increase the risk of Alzheimer\'s and some other dementias.\r\n\r\nOmega 3 supports blood clotting, dilates blood vessels and is anti-inflammatory, prevents heart disease and stroke, controls lupus, eczema and arthritis.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, omega 3 is also recognized by researchers to help prevent and slow down cancers.\r\n\r\nCan be used in salad dressings, salads, salads or on its own. Should not be used for frying because the oil is easily degraded at high temperatures.\r\n\r\nIdeally stored in the refrigerator, in a dry place, away from sources of heat and light due to its susceptibility to oxidation.\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% first cold pressed organic flaxseed oil.\r\n\r\nOrigin: Spain\r\n\r\nEuropean organic agriculture certification.', 3, 'img222.png', 100),
(226, 'Arrowhead Organic Red Lentils 453g', '7.00', 'Arrowhead Organic Red Lentils 100% Whole.\r\n- Cultivation technology is pure natural, biological, no zen modification, No use of plant preservatives, No use of chemical fertilizers and growth stimulants according to USDA standards.\r\nLentils have a particularly good nutritional profile for pregnant and lactating women. Children in developmental stage. People who need to diet, people who want to lose weight and just get sick. User manual\r\n- Soak lentils in water, then take them out to cook with rice, porridge, soup, make sauce...\r\n- Put in a pressure cooker to simmer, then cook with rice; puree to make cakes. Preserved in dry, cool place', 3, 'img223.png', 100),
