(228, 'Naturgreen Organic Pure Sesame Oil 250ml', '8.00', 'INGREDIENTS: 100% organic sesame oil\r\nDIRECTIONS FOR USE: Use as a substitute for regular cooking oil. Make sauces in salads, salads, etc.\r\nNaturgreen Organic Pure Sesame Oil is produced from organic ingredients, without the use of preservatives, additives and food colors. The product is certified organic from Europe.\r\n\r\nSesame seeds are a good source of calcium, vitamins E, B1, iron and are rich in fiber. Therefore, using sesame seed products has the effect of supporting laxatives, clearing heat, good for the heart and especially good for postpartum and premenopausal women.\r\n\r\nSesame seeds are rich in Omega 6 polyunsaturated fats: play an important role in ensuring the proper functioning of the brain and heart, and at the same time have the effect of reducing water loss in the skin, participating in strengthening and recovery. lipid layer, increasing the elasticity and softness of the skin.\r\n\r\nIn addition, sesame seed oil is rich in omega 9 monounsaturated fat (oleic acid): known as one of the ingredients to support the treatment and control of type 2 diabetes.\r\n\r\nELEMENT:\r\n\r\n100% organic sesame oil\r\n\r\nUSER MANUAL:\r\n\r\n- Use in place of regular cooking oil\r\n\r\n- Making sauces in salads, salads, etc.', 3, 'img225.png', 100),
(229, 'MARKAL ORGANIC SOYSYES 500G', '5.00', 'Characteristics :\r\n\r\n- Rich in fat and protein: a dietary supplement or/and meat substitute.\r\n\r\nSoybeans contain higher levels of vitamins A and E than other legumes.\r\n\r\n- Contains active ingredient lecithin: prevention and reduction of bad cholesterol.\r\n\r\nSoybeans contain isofalvone, a form of plant oestrogen, similar to œstradiol, a female hormone. Therefore, soy is often used as a dietary supplement to help relieve menopausal symptoms in women (hot flashes, irritability, sweating, osteoporosis, cardiovascular disease...).\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% organic yellow soybeans.\r\n\r\nUsage: Soak overnight. Cook soybeans for at least 3 hours to ensure digestibility. Do not eat raw.\r\n\r\nServe hot with rice or meat or cold as a salad with sauce.\r\n\r\nVietnamese food: cook tea, porridge, soup, nut milk, grind into powder...\r\n\r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from high heat and moisture. Better stored in glass jars.\r\n\r\nProducts imported directly from France.\r\n\r\nCertified organic by Agriculture Biologique and EU.', 3, 'img226.png', 100),
(230, 'Vinamit Organic Soybeans 1kg', '8.00', 'Organic Soybean Vinamit\r\n\r\nCharacteristics :\r\n\r\n- Rich in fat and protein: a dietary supplement or/and meat substitute.\r\n\r\nSoybeans contain higher levels of vitamins A and E than other legumes.\r\n\r\n- Contains active ingredient lecithin: prevention and reduction of bad cholesterol.\r\n\r\nSoybeans contain isofalvone, a form of plant oestrogen, similar to œstradiol, a female hormone. Therefore, soy is often used as a dietary supplement to help relieve menopausal symptoms in women (hot flashes, irritability, sweating, osteoporosis, cardiovascular disease...).\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% organic yellow soybeans.\r\n\r\nUsage: Soak overnight. Cook soybeans for at least 3 hours to ensure digestibility. Do not eat raw.\r\n\r\nServe hot with rice or meat or cold as a salad with sauce.\r\n\r\nVietnamese food: cook tea, porridge, soup, nut milk, grind into powder...\r\n\r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from high heat and moisture. Better stored in glass jars.', 3, 'img227.png', 100),
(231, 'Bioitalia organic cold pressed olive oil 250ml', '9.00', 'Ingredients: 100% organic cold pressed extra virgin olive oil\r\n\r\nOlive oil is a staple of the Mediterranean diet. However, today it is popular all over the world. This oil is rich in antioxidants. The fat itself is monounsaturated fatty acids (MUFAs), which experts consider healthy fats.\r\n\r\nThe antioxidants in olive oil can help protect the body from cell damage that can lead to a variety of health conditions and diseases. Extra virgin olive oil has a bitter taste, but it contains more antioxidants than other types, because it undergoes the least amount of processing.\r\n\r\nUsage: Cold pressed olive oil can be used in cooking. Cold pressed olive oil can be used to fry foods on low heat. It is also part of delicious salad dressing recipes.', 3, 'img227.png', 100),
(232, 'Markal Organic Green Beans 500g', '6.00', 'Characteristics:\r\n- High nutritional ingredients: rich in protid, starch, fat, fiber, vitamins E, B1, B2, B3, B6, vitamin C, provitamin K, folic acid and minerals including Ca, Mga, K, Na, Zn, iron...\r\n- Green bean pods contain many active ingredients belonging to the flavonoid group, which inhibit the growth of cancer cells, especially reducing the risk of breast and prostate cancer.\r\nAccording to oriental medicine, green beans have a sweet, slightly fishy taste, are cold, non-toxic, tonic, clear heat, cool the liver, detoxify...\r\nIngredients: 100% organic green beans.\r\nUser Manual:\r\n- Growing sprouts: Soak beans overnight. Then wash it off. Put the seeds in the planting tray, close the seeds, do not let the seeds overlap. Place the planting tray in a dark, cool, dry place, away from light. Germination time: 4-6 days.\r\n- Eat cold like a salad: Put 1 amount of beans and 3 amounts of water in the pot. Cook for 35 minutes.\r\n- Cook tea, porridge, soup, snack, roast vegetables to make powder... Store in a cool, dry place, avoid high heat and moisture. Better stored in glass jars. Products imported directly from France. Certified organic organic Agriculture Biologique.', 3, 'img228.png', 100),
(233, 'Markal Organic White Quinoa 500g', '9.00', 'PRODUCT INTRODUCTION Made directly in France\r\nINGREDIENTS 100% organic white quince\r\nUSES\r\n- Mild alkalinity, suitable for people who are following cancer treatment to inhibit the growth of cancer cells.\r\n- Gluten-free, suitable for people with gluten allergies or intolerances.\r\nA source of essential nutrients for the body: protein, fiber, vitamins and minerals. Especially, qui noa is one of the rare grains containing 9 essential amino acids for the body.\r\n Contains 2 flavonoids (Quercetine and Kaempferol), known for their antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, antiviral properties.\r\nContains poly sugars with a relatively low glycemic index (53), which aids in blood sugar control.\r\n USING\r\nWash the quinoa and cook for 10 minutes on low heat with twice the amount of water as the quino. Then turn off the heat, cover and let the quinoa seeds expand and absorb the water gradually. Can be used as salad, hot or cold, soup, milk, stir-fry with other vegetables...\r\nMETHODS OF PRESERVATION\r\nStore in a cool, dry place and avoid direct sunlight.', 3, 'img229.png', 100),
(234, 'Anh Dang Pure Alum Sugar 0.5kg', '2.00', 'No additives, no bleaching chemicals, no preservatives, so when you eat, you still feel the cool, sweet taste and do not cause sour mouth after use. Ingredients: 100% pure cane sugar syrup', 3, 'img230.png', 100),
(235, 'Exotic wild rice milled - 1kg', '4.00', 'USDA, EU organic approval\r\n\r\nPacking: Vacuum bag 1kg\r\n\r\nHoa Sua Organic Rice - Semi Exotic 1kg is rice that has partially removed the thin outer bran layer from Exotic black rice, the coarser inner bran layer remains. Rice has a light gray color, also known as wild pink rice.Rice milled rice retains most of the nutritional value of black rice such as rich in antioxidants, fiber, iron, omega 3, omega 6, good for humans. Because of the thin outer layer of bran no longer, the rice is softer and more flexible than Magic long grain black rice and drier than exotic rice of the same type. The new product is suitable for those of you who are used to using loose rice, which is a bit dry but still has a certain stickiness. Regarding the glycemic index, the G/I index of milled rice is higher than Magic black rice but lower than white rice and brown rice. The product is packaged by vacuum technology, so the risk is completely eliminated. contamination with aflatoxin mycotoxins - which is a carcinogen - that cannot be guaranteed during the production, transportation and packaging of conventional brown rice products.', 3, 'img231.png', 100),
(236, 'ST25 Ong Cua Organic Rice Box 2 kg', '7.00', 'ST25 organic rice meets the organic rice standards of the US and Europe and Japan (Organic USDA; EU Standard & JAS). Organic ST25 rice has elongated grains, gives soft rice, keeps the grains, has a characteristic light aroma, very different to eat. ST25 rice is cultivated according to the RICE - SHRIMP model (Shrimp farming in the dry season - in the rainy season, freshwater prawn farming is intercropped with rice fields).\r\n\r\nTo achieve organic standards, ST25 Organic Rice has passed 255 strict testing criteria from testing soil samples, water samples during the growing process to excess plant protection fertilizers.\r\n\r\nProduct information:\r\nFeatures: Rice makes the rice soft, supple, the rice retains the grain, the natural aroma, the rice is still delicious when cooled.\r\nWeight: Box 2kg\r\nCertification: USDA, EU, JAS\r\nBrand: Ong Cua Rice\r\nMade in Vietnam\r\nHow to cook ST25 organic rice\r\n1. Put the rice in the pot, put clean water in and wash it well to remove the dust, then pour out the water and wash it again like the first time.\r\n\r\n2. After washing the rice, add water to the pot to cook. The amount of water in the pot is as follows:\r\n\r\nThe first time you cook this type of rice, you can use a 1:1 ratio (100g rice / 100ml water).\r\nThe next time will adjust the water according to the user\'s taste.\r\n3. After the rice is cooked, don\'t lift the pot right away, but wait for another 5-10 minutes before taking it out to use.\r\n\r\nST25 Rice Organic Farming (Organic)\r\nST25 rice is grown according to organic farming methods, without the use of chemical fertilizers, pesticides, herbicides, etc., with the control and impact of science, technology and biotechnology. Products are processed and packaged according to a closed process.\r\n\r\nRice fields are grown on saline soil: in the dry season, shrimp are raised, and rice is washed in the rain. Due to the awareness of keeping a good environment for the successful shrimp farming following crop, farmers follow the organic production process very well.', 3, 'img232.png', 100),
(237, 'Wild Exotic Hoa Sua Black Brown Rice - 1kg', '5.00', 'Exotic Hoa Sua wild rice belongs to the wild rice line, soft, slightly flexible, with a characteristic aroma. This is a line of rice rich in antioxidants, fiber, iron, omega 3, omega 6, magnesium... good for people with anemia, heart disease, cancer, obesity.\r\n\r\nRegular pot:\r\n- Wash the rice once\r\n- Put rice and water in the ratio 1:1.5\r\n- Add a few drops of olive oil and a little sea salt to make the rice taste better.\r\n\r\nPressure cooker:\r\n- The same principle as above but for rice and water in the ratio 1:1\r\n- Adjust the cooking time between 25 - 30 minutes.\r\n\r\nCooking rice according to the Ohsawa method of nutrition:\r\n- Wash the rice once.\r\n- Soak the rice for 20-22 hours, add new water according to the ratio of 1 rice: 0.8 water.\r\n- Add a few drops of olive oil and a little sea salt to make the rice taste better.', 3, 'img233.png', 100),
(238, 'Hoa Sua (Magic) organic black brown rice 1Kg', '3.00', 'Made in Viet Nam\r\nCertified organic USDA, EU\r\nPacking: Vacuum bag 1kg\r\n \r\n \r\nHoa Sua Organic Magic Black Rice is a type of Magic Wild Rice that has been husked, unmilled, and is good for health because it retains most of the nutrients and a large amount of fiber and other elements. Micronutrients are located in the bran layer, when cooked, there is a light aroma, the rice is soft and spongy.\r\n \r\nIn the food group dubbed the Superfood of the 21st century because of its great health benefits, organic black rice has a harmonious ratio between essential nutritional ingredients: protein, vitamins, minerals. , fiber should both provide immediate energy but not increase blood fat; Contains a lot of fiber, so it is good for the digestive system and helps reduce bad cholesterol levels, control blood sugar levels.\r\n \r\nIn addition, there are biologically active substances, groups of Omega 3 and Omega 6 fatty acids that the body cannot synthesize, which is very good for the skin, brain, eyesight, joints, preventing the risk of atherosclerosis and cardiovascular disease. More than 120 antioxidants have strong effects on free radicals, have the effect of preventing and supporting the treatment of cancer, cardiovascular disease, diabetes, and effective weight loss...', 3, 'img234.png', 100),
(239, 'Hoa Sua organic brown rice - 1kg', '4.00', 'PRODUCT INTRODUCTION\r\nHoa Sua organic brown rice is produced in a closed process, meeting international standards, completely keeping the nutrition of rice. Rice is separated from the husk and retains the bran layer, which is very good for health.\r\n\r\nHoa Sua organic brown rice is also completely vacuum sealed, ensuring hygiene and extending the shelf life of the product.\r\n\r\nCHARACTERISTICS\r\nHoa Sua Organic Brown Rice, when cooked, has a characteristic aroma, soft and spongy rice grains.\r\n\r\nUSES\r\nHoa Sua Organic Brown Rice is very good for health, helping to reduce the incidence of cardiovascular diseases, diabetes, cancer control, cholesterol reduction, etc.\r\n\r\nUSING\r\nCook with the ratio of 1 rice: 2 water. You can soak for 30 minutes to soften the rice grains. When cooking, you should add a few drops of olive oil (vegetable oil) and less salt to make the rice more delicious.\r\n\r\nMETHODS OF PRESERVATION\r\nStore in a cool and dry place, avoid direct sunlight.', 3, 'img235.png', 100),
(240, 'Organic Brown Rice 1Kg', '3.00', 'Organic milled brown rice is cultivated under strict organic processes, complying with international standards EU - Europe USDA - USA AS - Japan\r\nDo not use chemical fertilizers, pesticides, herbicides\r\nUse only regulated organic fertilizers.\r\nThe place where rice is grown is the intersection of the lower Mekong River and the East Sea, with a specific climate, so each grain of rice is imbued with sweet taste, natural fragrance with many essential minerals.\r\n  Organic brown rice is produced from ST24 rice variety, meets the standards of long grain, clear white, medium plasticity and smells of pandan leaves; reached the top 3 best rice in the world at the International Rice Trade Conference 2017.', 3, 'img236.png', 100),
(241, 'Vigigaba Black Garlic Sprout Rice 1kg', '7.00', 'Net weight: 1kg\r\nOrigin: An Giang, Vietnam\r\nProduction date: See packaging\r\nExpiry date: 12 months\r\nPacking: Vacuum pack 1Kg\r\nBrand: Vibigaba\r\nIngredients: Sprouted brown rice, black garlic, peas, carrots\r\nColor: light brown mixed with orange, green, and white of vegetables\r\nProduce: Loc Troi\r\nStorage: Normal temperature, avoid direct sunlight\r\nVibigaba Black Garlic Germ Rice is rice that has its embryos intact for germination in the right conditions so that the enzymes in the rice grain are activated to create many nutrients, especially the natural Gaba content is 6 10 times higher than that of other rice varieties. brown. Rice also adds Black Garlic and lotus seeds to help promote the health protection features of sprouted rice.\r\nRice is grown in a concentrated raw material area, processed according to the European HACCP process, surpassing 603 strict Japanese criteria, ensuring a clear origin, quality commitment to consumers.\r\nEffects of Vibigaba Black Garlic germ rice:\r\nVibigaba Black Garlic Germ Rice Box 1Kg - Support to reduce blood fat, liver fat, enhance resistance, stabilize blood sugar and blood pressure\r\nHelps reduce blood fat, liver fat\r\nStrengthen resistance\r\nAnti-aging\r\nDelicious\r\nNutritional composition of Vibigaba Black Garlic germ rice\r\nCarbohydrates 600g\r\nProtein 70 g\r\nLipids 20 g\r\nDigestible fiber 30 g\r\nGaba 120-200 mg\r\nInositol 100 mg\r\nCalcium 50 mg\r\nVitamin B1 3 mg\r\nVitamin E 3 mg\r\nGlycemic Index GI (%) 58 ± 4.3 (compared to Glucose)\r\nQuality criteria\r\nHumidity : 14.5%\r\nPlate ratio : < 7%\r\nHow to cook Vibigaba Black Garlic sprout rice\r\nVibigaba sprout rice is very simple to cook\r\nNo need to wash the rice before cooking\r\nJust put rice and water into the pot according to the volume ratio of 1 Rice: 2 Water, or more depending on the customer\'s taste.\r\nIt\'s better to eat rice when it\'s hot', 3, 'img237.png', 100),
(242, 'Vibigaba sprout rice 1kg box', '4.00', 'VIBIGABA sprouted rice is a finished product from germinated brown rice, opaque yellow color, one end of the rice grain has a small chisel. When cooked, germ rice is sweeter and easier to eat than brown rice, in addition, sprouted rice also contains more nutrients than brown rice.', 3, 'img238.png', 100);
