(258, 'Organic Seeds Mixed 3 Kinds of Organic Nuts Sotto 250g', '4.00', 'Mixture of 3 types: brown flax, golden flax, chia seed Is a unique new product, combining super seeds rich in omega 3, fiber, amino acids for you in a macrobiotic, clean or healthy diet. vegetarian. Flaxseed is a source of omega 3, B vitamins, magnesium, phosphorus: helps the cardiovascular system to work properly, strengthens hair, nails and skin, boosts the immune system.\r\n- A source of omega 3, B vitamins, magnesium, phosphorus: helps the cardiovascular system work well, helps hair, nails and skin be strong, boosts the immune system.\r\n- Contains high fiber content, helps improve constipation, helps protect digestive mucosa.\r\n- Rich in lignans, phyto-oestrogens: anti-oxidants, prevent the growth of stem cells, limit the growth of hormone-related cancer cells (breast cancer, prostate cancer, endometrial cancer...).\r\nHelps improve type 1 and 2 diabetes.\r\n- Helps reduce bad cholesterol.\r\nOmega 3 has high anti-inflammatory properties, so it can reduce acne. Chia seeds contain a large amount of omega 3, which helps to lower cholesterol, maintain cardiovascular function and reduce the risk of heart diseases, help blood circulation, prevent arteriosclerosis as well as stroke. A great source of antioxidants for the body Helps reduce bad cholesterol. Directions for use: Use sprinkled on smoothies, juices, milk, salads. Increase the amount of vitamins and omega 3 for the body. Use sprinkles on crispy breads to add flavor to the dish.\r\n- Can be eaten whole, pounded or pureed depending on preferences and needs. Ground flaxseeds are better absorbed.\r\n- Serve with coleslaw, breakfast cereals, yogurt, smoothies or sauces. Add some to bread dough and cake recipes. Make flaxseed salt like sesame salt, serve with hot rice.', 3, 'img254.png', 100),
(259, 'Organic Seeds Mixed 4 Kinds of Organic Nuts Sottolestelle 250g', '6.00', 'Flaxseed is a source of omega 3, B vitamins, magnesium, phosphorus: helps the cardiovascular system to work properly, strengthens hair, nails and skin, boosts the immune system.\r\nA source of omega 3, B vitamins, magnesium, phosphorus: helps the cardiovascular system work well, helps hair, nails and skin be strong, boosts the immune system.\r\nContains high fiber content, helps improve constipation, helps protect digestive mucosa.\r\nRich in lignans, phyto-oestrogens: anti-oxidants, inhibit the growth of stem cells, limit the growth of hormone-related cancer cells (breast cancer, prostate cancer, endometrial cancer).\r\nHelps improve type 1 and 2 diabetes.\r\n\r\n- Helps reduce bad cholesterol.\r\n\r\nOmega 3 has high anti-inflammatory properties, so it can reduce acne.\r\nChia seeds contain a large amount of omega 3, which helps to lower cholesterol, maintain cardiovascular function and reduce the risk of heart diseases, help blood circulation, prevent arteriosclerosis as well as stroke.\r\n- A great source of antioxidants for the body\r\n- Helps reduce bad cholesterol.\r\n\r\nIngredients: Organic Sunflower Seeds, Organic Pumpkin Seeds, Organic Brown Flax Seeds, Organic Sesame Seeds\r\nUser manual:\r\nUse sprinkled in smoothies, juices, milk, salads. Increase the amount of vitamins and omega 3 for the body.\r\nUse sprinkles on crispy breads to add flavor to the dish.\r\nCan be mixed into baking powders to make cakes, breads, etc.\r\n– Can be eaten whole, crushed or pureed depending on preferences and needs. Ground flaxseeds are better absorbed.\r\n– Eat with coleslaw, breakfast cereals, yogurt, smoothies or sauces. Add some to bread dough and cake recipes. Make flaxseed salt like sesame salt, serve with hot rice.\r\n\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nShelf Life: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan\r\nNon-GMO', 3, 'img255.png', 100),
(260, 'Organic Seeds Mixed 7 Kinds of Organic Nuts Sottolestelle 400g', '7.00', 'A source of essential nutrients for the body: protein, fiber, vitamins and minerals. Especially, qui noa is one of the rare grains containing 9 essential amino acids for the body.\r\nContains 2 flavonoids (Quercetine and Kaempférol), known for their antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, antiviral properties.\r\nContains poly sugars with a relatively low glycemic index (53), which aids in blood sugar control. Provides great energy, calcium, magnesium, fat, protein, iron and many other nutrients. Supplementing with a high vitamin content is very good for eyesight, digestive system, helps children increase resistance, physical development, antioxidant and eliminates toxic substances from the body.\r\n \r\nElement:\r\nOrganic white quinoa, organic red quinoa, organic quinoa, organic shelled millet, shelled organic red lentils, organic sunflower seeds, organic pumpkin seeds\r\n \r\nUser manual:\r\nSoak the water for 30-60 minutes before cooking. Then stew for about 34 - 60 minutes. Near the end can add a little salt. Suitable for making soups or salads Can be used to cook rice or porridge, especially for babies, the elderly or simply eat to improve health.\r\n*Preserved in dry, cool place. Avoid sources of high heat and humidity. Better stored in glass jars. Seal tightly after each use.\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nShelf Life: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan\r\nNon-GMO', 3, 'img256.png', 100),
(261, 'Shelled Organic Hemp Seeds Sottolestelle 250g', '11.00', 'Hemp seeds are harvested from the hemp family (scientific name Cannabis sativa L). While hemp is often confused with cannabis, as it belongs to the same family, the two are quite different. Most notable was the THC or delta-9-tetrahydrocannabinol (psychoactive compound) content. Hemp contains less than 1% of psychoactive substances (such as THC) while cannabis has 20% or more of these substances. Therefore, the use of hemp seeds is legal and safe.\r\n\r\nHemp seeds contain a large amount of protein that helps strengthen the immune system, thereby reducing disease, in addition, it also helps to remove toxins from the body.\r\n\r\nThere is no other food substance that can contain such a large number of essential fatty acids as found in hemp seeds.\r\n\r\nHemp seeds have a balanced ratio of Omega 3 and 6 fats with a ratio of about 3:1 – the ideal ratio recommended by WHO and Health Canada for heart health and are free of seeds or oils. any other object containing this ratio.\r\n\r\nIf you want to maintain a healthy body, you should use hemp seeds, because they are rich in essential fatty acids. Moreover, hemp seeds produce phytosterols, which help reduce cholesterol in the body, so it also removes fatty deposits in the arteries.\r\n\r\nSottolestelle organic peeled hemp seeds have high nutritional value and contain more than 20 different amino acids and contain all 9 essential amino acids for the body. In particular, some essential amino acids cannot be produced naturally in the human body and they are capable of providing additional supplies for the body.\r\n\r\nYou can incorporate this hemp seed into your diet by:\r\n\r\n– Sprinkle seeds on cereal or yogurt\r\n– Add seeds to smoothies\r\n– Roast hemp seeds and other seeds rich in omega-3s\r\n– Make hemp milk\r\n– Sprinkle hemp seeds, along with other seeds on the salad\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% organic hemp seeds\r\n\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nShelf Life: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan\r\nNon-GMO', 3, 'img257.png', 100),
(262, 'Markal Organic Almonds - Pack of 250g', '11.00', 'INGREDIENTS 100% organic almonds\r\nNet weight: 250g\r\nUSES\r\n- Balance cholesterol in the body\r\n- Improve memory, increase blood circulation\r\n- Good for the cardiovascular system\r\n- Balance and regulate blood pressure\r\n- Effective weight loss\r\n- Lease school\r\n- Beautify the skin and strengthen the immune system\r\n- Very good for pregnant women and the comprehensive development of children\r\nHOW TO USE Almonds can be used directly in combination with salads, cakes, ..\r\nHOW TO STORAGE Store in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight', 3, 'img258.png', 100),
(263, 'OTS Organik Almonds 200g', '12.00', 'Ingredients: 100% organic raw almonds.\r\nOrigin: Turkey.\r\nDirections for use: Use alone or in combination with other recipes.\r\nStorage: Store in a cool, dry place.', 3, 'img259.png', 100),
(264, 'ORGANIC TIGER TIGER nut (EARTH ALMOND) 100g', '6.00', 'Diet Food Organic Tiger Nuts (ground almonds) 100g\r\n\r\nOrigin: Poland\r\n\r\nEU organic certification\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% organic tiger nuts\r\n\r\nThe tiger nut, also known as chufa, golden almond or ground almond, is not actually a nut but an edible tuber. They are about the size of a green pea but wrinkled with a chewy texture and sweet flavor similar to coconut.', 3, 'img260.png', 100),
(265, 'Shelled Organic Sunflower Seeds Sottolestelle 250g', '4.00', 'An oily seed, rich in polyunsaturated fats: prevents cardiovascular disease.\r\nRich in minerals necessary for the body such as phosphorus, magnesium, iron, ...\r\nContains plant sterols (phytosterols) that are effective against bad cholesterol.\r\nNatural source of vitamin E: contributes to preventing the development of free radicals and strengthening the immune system.\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% Shelled Organic Sunflower Seeds\r\nUser manual:\r\nEat separately, dry roast, mix salads, cereals, ingredients for making tea, soups, cakes, nut milks, etc. Store in a cool, dry place, avoid high temperature and humidity.\r\nAdd sunflower seeds to a veggie burger, and the meatballs are delicious, too.\r\n*Some people also like to roast sunflower seeds. You can do this by boiling 1 cup of the seeds in salted water for 5 to 10 minutes. Let the seeds dry in a baking pan and sprinkle with a pinch of salt. Bake the seeds at about 170°C for 25 minutes or until the pods are brown\r\n*Mix shelled seeds with vegetables for a delicious and nutritious salad\r\n*Toasting seeds with breads\r\n*Piece the seeds to make sunflower butter.\r\nDue to the high fat content, sunflower seeds are very easy to go rancid. Therefore, care should be taken to store them at a cool temperature.\r\n\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nShelf Life: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan\r\nNon-GMO', 3, 'img261.png', 100),
(266, 'Shelled Organic Millet Markal 500g', '6.00', 'PRODUCT INTRODUCTION\r\n- An alkaline grain, rich in protein: an excellent source of complementary and alternative food for vegetarian, macrobiotic, low-meat diets,\r\n- Source of B vitamins: aids in energy metabolism, enzyme and nervous system activity, participates in the production of red blood cells.\r\n- Gluten-free, suitable for people with gluten allergies or intolerances.\r\nELEMENT\r\n100% shelled organic millet\r\nUSING\r\nPour a sufficient amount of millet into the pot, add 2 times the amount of water as the millet. Then cook until the water boils, season to taste, cover the pot, reduce the heat and cook for another 20 minutes until the millet has absorbed all the water. Can be eaten hot or cold as salad, soup, sticky rice, tea, substitute or mixed with rice...\r\nMETHODS OF PRESERVATION\r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight', 3, 'img262.png', 100),
(267, 'Markal Organic Brown Flax Seeds 500g', '5.00', 'INGREDIENTS 100% organic brown flaxseed\r\nUSES\r\nFlaxseeds are rich in Ligan, fiber, omega3, vitamins and minerals such as vitamin B1, copper, molybdenum, magnesium, and phosphorus.\r\nProtects against prostate, colon and breast cancer.\r\nPrevents the growth of cancer cells because omega-3 fatty acids have the effect of breaking down malignant cells that attach to other cells of the body.\r\nLignan in flaxseed has anti-angiogenic properties\r\n– prevent tumors from forming new blood vessels.\r\nUSING\r\nFinely ground flaxseeds into a powder is better because lignans are best absorbed.\r\n- Flaxseed powder can be mixed with plain water, juice or milk. In addition, flaxseed flour can be used to make cakes instead of flour.\r\n- Can be roasted for use in salads, fruit smoothies, energy drinks, yogurts, mixed with breakfast cereals, mixed with mayonnaise while making bread, baking, cakes and pies Styrofoam…\r\nMETHODS OF PRESERVATION\r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight', 3, 'img263.png', 100),
(268, 'Markal Organic Golden Flax Seeds 500g', '5.00', 'ELEMENT\r\n100% organic golden flaxseed\r\nUSES\r\nFlaxseeds are rich in Ligan, fiber, omega3, vitamins and minerals such as vitamin B1, copper, molybdenum, magnesium, and phosphorus.\r\nProtects against prostate, colon and breast cancer.\r\nPrevents the growth of cancer cells because omega-3 fatty acids have the effect of breaking down malignant cells that attach to other cells of the body.\r\nLignan in flaxseed has anti-angiogenic properties – preventing tumors from forming new blood vessels.\r\nUSING\r\nFinely ground flaxseeds into a powder is better because lignans are best absorbed.\r\n- Flaxseed powder can be mixed with plain water, juice or milk. In addition, flaxseed flour can be used to make cakes instead of flour.\r\n- Can be roasted for use in salads, fruit smoothies, energy drinks, yogurts, mixed with breakfast cereals, mixed with mayonnaise while making bread, baking, cakes and pies Styrofoam…\r\nMETHODS OF PRESERVATION\r\nStore in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight', 3, 'img264.png', 100),
(269, 'Organic Whole Grain Grains Sottolestelle 500g', '5.00', 'Whole-grain rye is considered more nutritious than wheat because it\'s high in minerals with less carbohydrates and doesn\'t cause blood sugar spikes. Rye is an excellent source of fiber with 16.7g in a 100g serving. The addition of fiber helps reduce carbohydrate absorption, which helps prevent blood sugar levels from rising rapidly. Rye has a great impact on body weight; It prevents weight gain and reduces the risk of obesity. According to a study, rye improves insulin sensitivity and lowers total cholesterol in whole grain rye plasma, especially barley bread is effective in controlling glucose levels and improving insulin action. .\r\n \r\nIngredients: 100% organic wholegrain rye flour Directions for use: Soak in 2 parts water for 10 hours before cooking (or soak overnight) Rinse and drain, ratio 1 grain to 3 water, bring to a boil , reduce heat and cook for 50-60 minutes until the wheat is soft and cooked through. Can be mixed into salads or used with other dishes such as casseroles, soups, stews ... Can be ground into a powder to make bread, pies, ...\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nShelf Life: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan\r\nNon-GMO', 3, 'img265.png', 100),
(270, 'Shelled Organic Sesame Seeds Sottolestelle 250g', '5.00', 'Certified Organic Europe ICEA Certified Organic Non-GMO Vegan Source of calcium, vitamins E, B1, iron.\r\nSesame seeds contain about 55% unsaturated fatty acids, support to improve cardiovascular circulation, anti-inflammatory, stimulate scar healing, skin regeneration, increase the body\'s resistance.\r\n\r\nRich in fiber: support laxative, treat constipation, bloating, help clear heat. Contains phyto-oestrogens (sesamin and sesamolin): supports the maintenance of healthy cardiovascular activity, improves symptoms of discomfort during perimenopause in women.\r\n\r\n For women after giving birth, sesame is an indispensable ingredient to process foods, soups, teas, and milk with milky properties that are both safe and effective.\r\n\r\nSesame seeds contain phytosterols, a substance with a chemical structure similar to cholesterol, so it has the ability to reduce cholesterol in the blood.\r\n\r\nAs a seed that contains many antioxidants, at the same time, sesame seeds also improve the ability to protect and absorb vitamin E.\r\n\r\nThe calcium and zinc content in sesame seeds help build bones, increase bone strength\r\n\r\nThe B vitamins found in sesame: B1, B2, B3, B6, B9… are essential for the formation and operation of red blood cells, the functioning of the nervous system, and supporting the body in energy metabolism.\r\n\r\n According to Chinese medicine, the eyes and liver have an intimate relationship. It is believed that the liver can store blood, and the limbs of the liver supply blood to the eyes. Sesame seeds are a natural tonic for the liver, allowing better blood flow to the eyes, thus believed to nourish the eyes. The effects of sesame help reduce blurred vision, eye fatigue and pain', 3, 'img266.png', 100),
(271, 'Bio Smart Organic Walnuts - 200g', '10.00', 'Smart Organic Shelled Walnuts 200g\r\n\r\nProduct information:\r\n\r\n- Organic certification body: Nutramed LTD\r\n\r\n- European organic certification, BG-BIO-22\r\n\r\n- Distributor and manufacturer: Smart Organic\r\n\r\n- Weight: 200g\r\n\r\n- Material from: Bulgaria\r\n\r\n- Enter words: Bulgaria\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% organic walnuts\r\n\r\nAttention: Store in a cool and dry place\r\n\r\nNutritional ingredients:\r\n\r\nWalnuts can be considered the king of nuts for health and beauty benefits, surpassing almonds, pecans, hazelnuts, pistachios and many other nutritious nuts. Walnuts contain almost twice as much antioxidants as other nuts, and are packed with high-quality protein.\r\n\r\nRegular use of walnut oil and eating walnuts can prevent hair loss, causing baldness. Besides, walnut oil is widely used in the production of hair oils due to its rich moisturizing properties, as a natural anti-dandruff agent.', 3, 'img267.png', 100),
(272, 'OTS Organik Organic Hazelnuts 200g', '10.00', 'Rich in monounsaturated fatty acids and low in saturated and polyunsaturated fatty acids: helps reduce bad cholesterol in the body.\r\n- Famous for its very high antioxidant capacity (TAC Total Antioxidant Capacity): tannins, phenolic acids, flavonoids, manganese and vitamin E.\r\n- Source of essential nutrients for the body: iron, fiber, vitamin B1, magnesium.', 3, 'img268.png', 100),
(273, 'Fresh Lotus Seeds 200g', '3.00', 'Lotus seeds are the seeds of plants of the genus Lotus, they are located in the lotus calyx. After the flower fades, the lotus is harvested to get the fruit, peeled off the lotus seed. Lotus seeds are often used in both forms, fresh seeds and dried seeds with great nutritional value inside. Nutritional ingredients in lotus seeds include: starch, protein, fat, vitamins and minerals such as vitamin B2 (riboflavin), sodium, potassium, calcium, magnesium, phosphorus ... and does not contain cholesterol. Fresh lotus seeds are one of the popular ingredients of Vietnamese dishes from nutritious dishes such as stews to desserts such as lotus seed longan tea.', 3, 'img269.png', 100),
(274, 'Organic super sorghum (bobo) seeds Sottolestelle 500g', '6.00', 'Their high nutritional value and many uses, especially gluten-free, make them a nutritious food source for many people.\r\nIn its whole grain form, this grain can be cooked like quinoa or rice, ground into a flour, or popped like popcorn. It can also be made into syrup for use as a sweetener in canned foods.\r\nThis cereal is packed with nutrients, including B vitamins, which play an essential role in metabolism, nerve development, and skin and hair health.\r\nIt\'s also a rich source of magnesium, a mineral important for bone formation, heart health, and more than 600 biochemical reactions in the body (such as energy production and protein metabolism). .\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% Organic Super Sorghum (bobo) Seeds\r\nUser manual:\r\nSoak super sorghum seeds in water for 12 hours to reduce cooking time. Put 4 times the amount of water in the pot. When the water boils, reduce the heat and cook for another 45 minutes.\r\nYou can use sorghum in so many ways and easily add them to many recipes.\r\n*Preserved in dry, cool place. Avoid sources of high heat and humidity. Better stored in glass jars. Seal tightly after each use.', 3, 'img270.png', 100),
(275, 'Organic Earth Tiger Nuts (Earth Almonds) 100g', '6.00', 'Tiger nuts, also known as chufa, golden almonds or ground almonds, are not actually a nut but an edible tuber. They are about the size of a green pea but wrinkled with a chewy texture and sweet flavor similar to coconut.', 3, 'img271.png', 100),
(276, 'Organic Sottolestelle (Bobo) Seeds 500g', '6.00', 'Licorice or pearl barley is a species of tall, seed-bearing tropical plant in the family Herbaceae. It is also known as bo bo, but it should be noted that this is not bo bo during the subsidy period. Bo bo during the subsidy period was a high salary.\r\n \r\nUses: Willow seeds help strengthen the spleen, stomach and bring many benefits to the lungs by preventing infections, relieving colds. This seed also nourishes healthy skin, removes wrinkles, promotes health and prolongs life. It has the ability to reduce the amount of toxins accumulated in the body. Therefore, in the remedies containing willow seeds will bring diuretic ability, treat edema, solve bacteria that cause lung infections and diseases related to the digestive tract such as: Diarrhea, flatulence , full stomach.\r\n \r\nIngredients: 100% organic Italian seeds\r\n \r\nUser manual:\r\nSoak the leeks in water for 12 hours to reduce cooking time. Put 4 times the amount of water in the pot. When the water boils, reduce the heat and cook for another 45 minutes.\r\n- Can be used cold as salad, eaten instead or whole with rice, cooked porridge, baby food...\r\n- Addition flour for bread and baking recipes. Preserved in dry, cool place. Avoid sources of high heat and humidity. Better stored in glass jars. Seal tightly after each use.\r\n– Can be used to cook porridge to help benefit milk for women after giving birth by making 30g yellow seeds, stewing with pork leg and holding glutinous rice.\r\nOrigin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nShelf Life: 24 months from date of manufacture\r\nCertified European Organic Vegan Non-GMO', 3, 'img272.png', 100),
(277, 'Shelled Organic Oats Sottolestelle 500g', '6.00', 'Certified European Organic Certified Organic Italia Vegan Non-GMO Rich in fiber, which helps eliminate and eliminate toxins and harmful excess fats that clog the body and cause overweight. Contains a large amount of minerals such as iron, sodium, zinc, magnesium, potassium, folic acid ..., which help nourish the body and maintain tissues. Helps reduce bad cholesterol.\r\nOats are known as a nutritious and extremely healthy cereal with miraculous multi-purpose uses.\r\n\r\n- Rich in fiber, which helps to eliminate and eliminate toxins and harmful excess fats that clog the body and cause overweight.\r\n\r\n- Contains a large amount of minerals such as iron, sodium, zinc, magnesium, potassium, folic acid ..., which help nourish the body and maintain tissues.\r\n\r\nOats are a great natural alternative to help absorb and eliminate harmful cholesterol, excess water and toxins, due to its soluble fiber.\r\n\r\nContains a large amount of Omega 6 and linoleic acid (nearly 35%) to help clean harmful cholesterol in the blood\r\n\r\n- Helps raise good cholesterol (HDL), helps to clear the veins and reduce weight.\r\n\r\n- Promotes satiety, helping to reduce excessive or uncontrolled hunger.\r\n\r\nA great source of antioxidants for the body\r\n\r\nHelps reduce bad cholesterol.\r\n\r\nOats also help enhance concentration, avoid neurasthenia, strengthen the body\'s immune system and are food for \"love\" because of its ability to enhance sex hormones.\r\n\r\nA diet with added oats will help protect your heart. This is confirmed by scientists from the University of Kentucky (USA). Accordingly, oats have properties that help lower blood cholesterol levels.\r\n\r\n- Oats have the effect of losing weight or used as a very effective whitening and exfoliating mask. According to general evaluation, the effect of masks with the main ingredient of oats is often many times faster than other types of masks.', 3, 'img273.png', 100),
(278, 'Bio Planet Organic Bean Mix 400g', '6.00', 'Bean mix is an organic blend of legumes, used in soups, stews, pates and pastes.\r\n\r\nIngredients: Chickpeas*, Chickpeas*, White Beans*, Black Beans*, Green Lentils*, Green Lentils (Small)*, Chickpeas*, Red Lentils* (*Organic Ingredients).\r\n\r\nInstructions for use: Soak the bean mixture for at least 12 hours, rinse with water. Boil the soaked bean mixture for about 60 minutes. Add salt when done cooking.\r\n\r\nStorage: Store in a cool, dry place, away from moisture and direct light.\r\n\r\nImported directly from Poland\r\n\r\nEU organic certification', 3, 'img274.png', 100),
(279, 'Organic Omega 3 Seed Blend Sottolestelle 250g', '6.00', 'Origin: Sottolestelle – Italy\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\nVegan Non-GMO\r\nIs a unique new product that combines super nuts rich in omega 3, fiber, amino acids for you in a macrobiotic, clean or vegetarian diet.\r\nIngredients: organic brown flax seeds, organic hulled hemp seeds, organic chia seeds Chia 100g: 30g chia seeds, 40g hemp seeds, 30g flax seeds\r\n \r\nUses: Flaxseed is a source of omega 3, B vitamins, magnesium, phosphorus: helps the cardiovascular system work well, helps hair, nails and skin be strong, boosts the immune system. Hem seeds have a nutty flavor similar to sunflower and pine nuts, but with a softer texture. It has high nutritional value and contains more than 20 different amino acids as well as: Omega-3, Omega-6, Stearidonic Acid (SDA), Omega-6 Linolenic Acid (GLA), Magnesium, Fiber, Iron, Zinc , Phosphorus, Contains a large amount of protein. Chia seeds contain a large amount of omega 3, which helps to lower cholesterol, maintain cardiovascular function and reduce the risk of heart diseases, help blood circulation, prevent arteriosclerosis as well as stroke. A great source of antioxidants for the body Helps reduce bad cholesterol. Omega 3 has high anti-inflammatory properties, so it can reduce acne. Directions for use: Use sprinkled on smoothies, juices, milk, salads. Increase the amount of vitamins and omega 3 for the body. Use sprinkles on crispy breads to add flavor to the dish.', 3, 'img275.png', 100),
(280, 'Bett\'r . Organic Chocolate Candy', '5.00', 'Ingredients: cane sugar*, cocoa mass*, cocoa butter*, rice starch*, food coloring (spirulina concentrate*, saffron, apple*, carrot*, radish*, black currants *), thickener: gum arabic *, coating agent: carnauba wax *.\r\n* From controlled organic farming.\r\nNutritional value per 100g:\r\nEnergy Value - 2075.4kJ / 496.4kcal\r\nFat - 25g\r\nwhere saturated fatty acids - 15g\r\nCarbohydrates - 61g\r\nin which sugar - 56g\r\nFiber - 6.1g\r\nProtein - 3.8g\r\nSalt - 0.0g\r\nProducer - Bulgaria', 3, 'img276.png', 100),
