(286, 'AmaVie Foods Organic Goji berries 170g', '7.00', 'Goji berry is a ripe or dried fruit of the plant, whose scientific name is Lycium barbarum L. (Lycium chinense mill). In ancient times, ancient people often called the sentence goji by beautiful names such as Thien Tinh (star of heaven), Di Tien (fairy of the earth), Khieu Lao (repelling old age) ... Ky Tu was also known as \"Ming Minh. death\", which means the fruit that brightens the eyes.\r\n\r\nSalient features:\r\n\r\n- Goji berry type 1, size 180 fruit/50g, large fruit, outstanding quality.\r\n\r\nGoji berries are rich in nutrients, vitamins, fiber, minerals, antioxidants and essential amino acids for the body.\r\n\r\nThe great nutritional values ​​of goji berries:\r\n\r\n- High natural antioxidant\r\n\r\n- Source of essential vitamins and nutrients: Goji berry contains 18 amino acids, 8 types of polysaccharide complex sugars (glucid - a source of energy for the body, activating the immune system and cardiovascular system), 5 types of carotenoids (including beta carotene - good for eyes and skin), 22 minerals and trace elements (phosphorus, calcium, potassium, iron, zinc, selenium; 6 vitamins: C, B2, B3, B6, B12 et E) .\r\n\r\nRich in phytosterols (plant sterols), goji berries help reduce blood pressure and bad cholesterol in the body, helping to reduce mild inflammation.\r\n\r\nGoji berries contain 13% more protein than wheat.', 3, 'img282.png', 100),
(287, 'Naturgreen Organic Goji berries 200g', '13.00', 'Ingredients: 100% organic goji berries\r\nOrigin: SPAIN\r\nUser manual :\r\n- Mix with cereal in breakfast.\r\n- Cook porridge or soup, stew with broth.\r\n- Cooking tea\r\n- Eat\r\n- Brew tea\r\nStore in a dry place away from high heat and moisture.\r\nEuropean organic certification', 3, 'img283.png', 100),
(288, 'Thnot Syrup Organic Honey Syrup 150ml', '3.00', 'Origin: Cambodia\r\nProducts are certified organic by USDA, EU, ECOCERT and many other reputable organizations.\r\nThe product is suitable for children over 1 year old, adults ...\r\nPalm nectar has a mild sweet taste, the bar does not cause throat irritation, and is fragrant.\r\nProduct Description\r\n- Confirel organic jaggery is produced from raw materials of fresh organic jaggery, without the use of industrial chemicals.\r\n- Produced by traditional methods, Confirel jaggery retains the full flavor of jaggery.\r\n- Enhances digestion.\r\nThe potassium content in jaggery helps reduce bloating and water retention, contributing to weight loss. Jaggery also contains many important nutrients such as vitamins and minerals needed by the body.\r\nElement:\r\n- 100% raw organic jaggery nectar\r\nUser manual:\r\n- Use as a substitute for cane sugar\r\n- Marinating meat, fish, processing dishes\r\n-Cooking tea, used in cake recipes\r\n- Make tea, coffee,…\r\n=> Moms can use regular cane sugar in daily cooking to create a sustainable health foundation for the family!', 3, 'img284.png', 100),
