(322, 'Bich Chi organic brown rice noodle soup box 200g', '3.00', 'The flat, brown noodles are made from brown rice flour, which is very convenient for preparing dishes such as stir-frying or using with broth. Bich Chi organic brown rice noodle soup box 200g just need to be boiled in boiling water to be used. Bich Chi dry noodle is convenient, trusted by many users\r\n\r\nProduct Type\r\nOrganic brown rice noodle soup\r\n\r\nWeight\r\n200g\r\n\r\nType of yarn\r\nFlat yarn, big\r\n\r\nElement\r\n100% organic brown rice. No chemical preservatives are used\r\n\r\nHow to use\r\nWash with clean water. Put the rice noodle in a pot of boiling water for about 6-8 minutes. Remove and rinse with clean water. Drain and mix well with a little oil before sautéing or cooking with meat, eggs, vegetables, etc.\r\n\r\nPreserve\r\nTo a dry, cool place\r\n\r\nTrademark\r\nBich Chi (Vietnam)\r\n\r\nMade in\r\nVietnam\r\n\r\nDry pho is no longer a strange dish to Vietnamese users, but have you ever heard of brown rice noodle soup? Today, Bich Chi brings to users an extremely delicious and nutritious 200g box of organic brown rice noodle soup.', 3, 'img318.png', 100),
(323, 'Maple Syrup 250ml', '15.00', 'New Zealand\'s BioGro certified organic Non - GMO, no preservatives No impurities, harmful chemicals Imported from Malaysia Safe to use\r\nMaple Syrup Maple Syrup brand Radiant with 100% Organic ingredients is safe to use for your family.\r\n\r\nMaple Syrup has a mild sweetness that is why they are often used as a substitute for honey. Maple syrup is often used with pastries such as pancakes, crepes, waffles, toasts, etc. When used to serve, maple syrup will be sprinkled directly on the surface of the cake for people to enjoy.\r\n\r\nIn addition to its use as a side dish, maple syrup is also used to spread on the surface of baked goods or baked goods before placing in the oven. After baking, the maple syrup layer on the outside will form an extremely delicious coating and increase the attractiveness of the dish as well as the cake. Maple syrup is also used directly with oats or cereals, this combination also gives a quite delicious and attractive taste.', 3, 'img319.png', 100),
(324, 'Organic Agave Agave Syrup 360g', '7.00', 'Origin: Spain European organic certification\r\nOrigin: Spain\r\n\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\n\r\nAgave syrup is a type of honey from the agave plant. Agave is a sweetening plant with high fructose content and low glycemic index. Consumption of foods containing fructose lowers blood sugar significantly more than foods containing sucrose or glucose.\r\n\r\nYou can use agave syrup to sweeten plant-based milk, breakfast cereals, and pancakes.\r\n\r\nSweetening products are very safe for health', 3, 'img320.png', 100),
