(347, 'Orange', '4.00', 'Organic Sanh Orange is a familiar orange of tropical Vietnam. Tangerine oranges are easy to recognize thanks to their thick, rough skin like a thin crockery surface, and are often pale green (when ripe, orange), the flesh is orange. Oranges at Organic are carefully selected from Organic\'s own farm which is certified by USDA, Organic EU, ensuring clean, no chemicals, no growth drugs, no genetically modified substances. There are many sizes according to weight, meeting the needs of customers, ... Oranges are large, succulent, sweet and sour, cool, ...\r\n\r\nUSES Oranges are rich in vitamin C, vitamin A, calcium, fiber ... very nutritious for the body of pregnant women. Vitamin B9 (folic acid) found in oranges is extremely important, especially for pregnant women or those trying to conceive. Oranges help prevent certain types of birth defects, increase resistance, and help produce healthy blood cells. In addition, the limonoid in orange juice helps prevent cancer and has detoxifying and diuretic effects.\r\nHOW TO STORAGE Refrigerate to keep products fresher longer', 5, 'img343.png', 100),
