(416, 'Sauceco Organic Vegetarian Oyster Oil 420ml', '13.00', 'Ingredients: organic wheat, organic soybeans, water, salt, sugar, organic glutinous rice, organic mushrooms, organic licorice\r\n\r\nExpiry date: 36 months from nsx\r\n\r\nOyster oil is a familiar condiment to Vietnamese people. This spice is added to stir-fries and stews to add natural sweetness and fatness to dishes.\r\n\r\nSauce Co oyster sauce is made from high quality organic ingredients, with a particularly delicious and attractive flavor that will make the dish very different.\r\n\r\nUsage: seasoning, marinating for stir-fried, braised dishes\r\n\r\nOrigin: Taiwan\r\n\r\nTaiwan organic certification', 6, 'img412.png', 100),
(417, 'IL NUTRIMENTO Organic Hemp Seed Oil 250ml', '13.00', 'Origin: Italy\r\n\r\nEU organic certification\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% cold pressed hemp seed oil\r\n\r\nIl Nutrimento Organic Hemp Seed Oil is obtained without preheating the seeds or presses prior to pressing and without the need for additional heat during extraction. It is rich in polyunsaturated fats and naturally rich in omega-3 fatty acids. Replacing saturated fats with unsaturated fats in the diet contributes to the maintenance of normal blood cholesterol levels. A varied and balanced diet and healthy lifestyle should be followed.\r\n\r\nUsage: Use directly in dishes, do not cook\r\n\r\nStorage: In the refrigerator after opening', 6, 'img413.png', 100),
(418, 'Naturgreen Organic Flaxseed Oil250ml', '8.00', 'Flaxseed oil is distinguished from other vegetable oils by its high content of omega 3, namely ALA (alpha-linoleic acid) and omega 9 (oleic acid) polyunsaturated fatty acids. In addition, flaxseed oil is also considered as the vegetable oil with the best omega 6/omega 3 ratio. As an alternative source of fish food, which contains a lot of omega 3. Suitable for vegetarian diets.\r\n\r\nFor fresh produce, the actual weight may vary by about 10%.\r\n\r\nFlaxseed oil is distinguished from other vegetable oils by its high content of omega 3, namely ALA (alpha-linoleic acid) and omega 9 (oleic acid) polyunsaturated fatty acids. In addition, flaxseed oil is also considered as the vegetable oil with the best omega 6/omega 3 ratio.\r\n\r\nAs an alternative source of fish food, which contains a lot of omega 3. Suitable for vegetarian diets.\r\n\r\nWhy is omega 3 good for the body?\r\n\r\nOmega 3 is one of the components that make up the mucous membranes that make up the cells in the body and helps the cells in their genetic activity.\r\n\r\nWhen absorbed by the body, ALA (alpha-linoleic acid) is converted into DHA (docosahexaenoic acid) and EPA (Eicosapentaenoic acid) to help improve type 2 diabetes.\r\n\r\nDHA is an indispensable ingredient for eye and nervous system development. DHA deficiency may increase the risk of Alzheimer\'s and some other dementias.\r\n\r\nOmega 3 supports blood clotting, dilates blood vessels and is anti-inflammatory, prevents heart disease and stroke, controls lupus, eczema and arthritis.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, omega 3 is also recognized by researchers to help prevent and slow down cancers.\r\n\r\nCan be used in salad dressings, salads, salads or on its own. Should not be used for frying because the oil is easily degraded at high temperatures.\r\n\r\nIdeally stored in the refrigerator, in a dry place, away from sources of heat and light due to its susceptibility to oxidation.\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% first cold pressed organic flaxseed oil.\r\n\r\nOrigin: Spain\r\n\r\nEuropean organic agriculture certification.', 6, 'img414.png', 100),
(419, 'Naturgreen Organic Pure Sesame Oil 250ml', '8.00', 'INGREDIENTS: 100% organic sesame oil\r\n\r\nDIRECTIONS FOR USE: Use as a substitute for regular cooking oil. Make sauces in salads, salads, etc. Naturgreen Organic Pure Sesame Oil is produced from organic ingredients, without the use of preservatives or additives. Food coloring and additives. The product is certified organic from Europe.\r\nSesame seeds are a good source of calcium, vitamins E, B1, iron and are rich in fiber. Therefore, using sesame seed products has the effect of supporting laxatives, clearing heat, good for the heart and especially good for postpartum and premenopausal women.\r\n\r\nSesame seeds are rich in Omega 6 polyunsaturated fats: they play an important role in ensuring the proper functioning of the brain and heart, and at the same time have the effect of reducing water loss in the skin, participating in strengthening and recovery. lipid layer, increasing the elasticity and softness of the skin.\r\n\r\nIn addition, sesame seed oil is rich in omega 9 monounsaturated fat (oleic acid): known as one of the ingredients to support the treatment and control of type 2 diabetes.\r\n\r\nELEMENT:\r\n\r\n100% organic sesame oil\r\n\r\nUSER MANUAL:\r\n\r\n- Use in place of regular cooking oil\r\n\r\n- Making sauces in salads and salads', 6, 'img415.png', 100),
(420, 'Bioitalia organic cold pressed olive oil 250ml', '10.00', 'Brand: BioItalia\r\n\r\nOrigin: Italy\r\n\r\nEuropean standard organic certification\r\n\r\nSpecification: 250ml bottle\r\n\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\n\r\nHSD: 18 months from date of manufacture\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% organic extra virgin olive oil. The oil contains many Omega-3 nutrients & the best natural micronutrients for children during the weaning period, pregnant women and users.\r\n\r\nInstructions for use: Add to baby food mixed with salad, skin care, hair ... Store in a dry place, avoid direct sunlight.', 6, 'img416.png', 100),
(421, 'Bioitalia Organic Cold Pressed Olive Oil 250ml', '10.00', 'The oil contains many Omega-3 nutrients & the best natural micronutrients for children during the weaning period, pregnant women and users.\r\n\r\n- Brand: BioItalia\r\n-Origin: Italy Certified organic European standard\r\n- Specification: 250ml bottle\r\n-European organic certification\r\nIngredients: 100% organic extra virgin olive oil.\r\n-Use: Add to baby food, salad, skin care, hair ...\r\n-Store in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight.', 6, 'img417.png', 100),
(422, 'Bragg Cold Pressed Organic Olive Oil 473ml', '15.00', 'Bragg is a world famous brand with famous apple cider vinegar products, did you know they also have very high quality Extra Virgin Olive oil?\r\n\r\nBragg\'s Organic Cold Pressed Extra Virgin Olive Oil is the world\'s finest premium quality oil. The world famous olive oil comes from 3 countries: Greece, Spain and Italy. While Italy is a country that consumes more olives than it produces, it usually imports olive oil from Greece and Spain to mix with its oil, while Greece exports only Olive oil. Bragg\'s Olive Oil is the Koroneiki variety from Greece. The Koroneiki variety has been grown in Greece for more than 3000 years, the soil and climate of the Mediterranean are suitable for the olive tree to grow and develop. This is the world\'s best and most fragrant olive oil variety. Normally, the standard Extra Virgin Olive Oil of the International Olive Oil Association IOOC is less than 0.8% acid, but Bragg Organic Extra Virgin Olive Oil is 0.51%, so the oil does not have a strong smell like other Olive oils because of its high acidity. except the refined olive oil has been neutralized, filtered, bleached making it almost odorless).\r\n\r\nIn particular, the Koroneiki variety also contains many polyphenols, which are many times more powerful antioxidants than other Olive varieties. Polyphenols help eliminate free radicals in the body, preventing cancer. It is because of the high polyphenol content that Extra Virgin Olive Bragg can be stored longer, more stable up to 24 months under normal conditions. The polyphenol content is 5 times higher than that of refined olive oil. Not only that, thanks to the high Polyphenols, the oil is stable to oxidizing agents, so the oil has a very high smoke point of 205 degrees Celsius.\r\n\r\nExtra Virgin is only the first pressed oil to bring out the best quality with the most nutrients. For Olive oil in general, there will be other types like Virgin/Pure/Pomance, only later pressings make the quality of the oil worse.\r\n\r\n– Cold pressing refers to the method of pressing oil that is not affected by oxidation by temperature.\r\n\r\n– Organic refers to the method of growing olives that are not contaminated by GMOs and chemicals.\r\n\r\n– Color: EVOO will have a darker color than other lines of Olive oil, EVOO Bragg has a very beautiful golden brown color.\r\n\r\nTaste: Taste is also a qualitative factor in determining whether olive oil is good or not. For good oil you can smell the smell of fresh olives.\r\n\r\nThe free acid index is an important indicator to evaluate the quality of olive oil. For the EVOO series according to the international standard of IOOC it is less than 0.8%, but for the EVOO Bragg it is 0.51% lower than the general standard. The reason olive oil is better, the lower this number is because the oil is actually an ester of a fatty acid. In the process of pressing under the effects of oxidizing oil, the bonds will be broken to create free acids. Thus, the free acid reflects the oxidizing effect of the cooking oil. The higher this number, the more oxidized the oil and the stronger the smell.\r\n\r\nBy determining this index will determine the quality of the EVOO, it is also an important parameter for people to be able to determine how fake EVOO oil is. In fact, there are many fake EVOOs on the market today.\r\n\r\nThe peroxide ratio determines the initial oxidation of an oil. Peroxidation is oxidation. Exposure to heat, light, and metal surfaces accelerates oil oxidation.\r\nThe lower this value, the longer the oil will retain its shelf life and will delay the possibility of going rancid, while a high peroxide value usually indicates poor handling and low quality of the oil. Thus Olive Oil has a low peroxide value which means it is more stable and if stored properly, the shelf life is extended.\r\nEVOO Bragg has a peroxide index of 10.8 meqO2/kg, while the standard of IOOC is <= 20 meqO2/kg', 6, 'img418.png', 100),
(423, 'Organic Coconut Sugar Organicfood.vn 250g', '2.00', 'The harmful effects of sugar have been proven and clearly seen in life. As a result, people are slowly turning to other natural alternatives. Among them, one sweetener that has become very popular over the past few years is coconut sugar. This sugar is derived from the coconut palm tree and is advertised as more nutritious and has a lower glycemic index than sugar.', 6, 'img419.png', 100),
(424, 'Thailand Wangkanai Organic Raw Cane Sugar 1kg', '3.00', 'Wangkanai Organic Cane Sugar is produced from safe organic raw materials.\r\nSugar is used to soak fruits, make drinks, cook, bake, make smoothies, etc.\r\nOrigin: Thailand\r\nWeight: 1kg\r\nProducts certified by USDA and Europe', 6, 'img420.png', 100),
(425, 'Anh Dang Pure Alum Sugar 500g', '2.00', 'No additives, no bleaching chemicals, no preservatives, so when you eat, you still feel the cool, sweet taste and do not cause sour mouth after use.\r\n\r\nIngredients: 100% pure cane sugar syrup', 6, 'img421.png', 100),
(426, 'Anh Dang Pure Alum Sugar1kg', '4.00', 'Ingredients: 100% pure cane sugar syrup.\r\n\r\nQuality criteria: Degree of Pol (at 20oC) ≥ 90. Moisture ≤ 3% by weight.\r\nNet weight: 500g/bag.\r\n How to use:\r\nCharacteristics of rock sugar: cool - sweet taste.\r\nUse as white granulated sugar.\r\nUsed in daily life: drinking coffee, iced lemon, orange juice, cooking tea, ...\r\nSeason common dishes: Pho, soup, noodle soup, noodles, hot pot, ...\r\nUsed to produce all kinds of beverage: bird\'s nest water, fruit juice, confectionery, ...\r\nUsed to produce spices such as soy sauce, fish sauce, dipping sauce, ...\r\nHow to taste: 3 tablespoons rock sugar + 2 tablespoons salt + 1/10 teaspoon MSG or seasoning powder.\r\nStorage Instructions: Store in a cool, dry place.\r\nFood safety warnings and warnings: Do not use the product after the expiry date, store the product according to the manufacturer\'s instructions.', 6, 'img422.png', 100),
(427, 'Confirel Organic Palm Sugar 500g', '5.00', 'Organic jaggery is made from the sap of the palm tree in Cambodia. Naturally processed and certified organic by USDA organic & EU standards can be used as a substitute for regular sugar.\r\nFeatures and uses:\r\n- Provides many minerals\r\nPalm sugar is rich in essential minerals. According to some research results, the mineral content in this sugar is 60 times higher than that of white granulated sugar. This is a food source of many different vitamins.\r\n- Restore health to the digestive system\r\nIt may sound strange, but jaggery has the ability to act as a digestive aid. In some parts of India, people have the habit of sipping small lumps of jaggery after the main meal for easy digestion. This type of sugar when entering the stomach will stimulate the activity of digestive enzymes and also help cleanse the intestines.\r\n- Rich in nutrients\r\nPalm sugar contains a lot of iron. Therefore, regular consumption will increase hemoglobin levels and cure anemia. In addition, the amount of magnesium has the effect of regulating the nervous system.\r\nThe rich antioxidant content in this natural sweetener also helps protect the body\'s cells from damage caused by free radicals. In addition, they are rich in calcium, potassium and phosphorus.\r\n– Extra energy\r\nPalm sugar contains carbohydrate compounds that help the body digest faster than white granulated sugar. Therefore, they will release stored energy if you use this sugar regularly. This also means that you will feel full for longer and have less appetite after consuming foods made with jaggery.\r\n- Treatment of some common diseases\r\nSince ancient times, jaggery has been used as medicine to treat various common ailments. To this day, they are still considered a folk remedy for colds and coughs by breaking down accumulated mucus and clearing the airways. If you suffer from respiratory diseases such as cough, asthma, etc., you can consult a traditional medicine 