(445, 'Sesame Salt Sprinkled with Rice Algae Flavor Sottolestelle 200g', '7.00', 'Goma is the Japanese word for sesame, and sio is the word for salt. As you might have guessed, gomasio is a combination of the two. It is sometimes called sesame salt. The sesame seeds in the gomasio are lightly toasted before being used in the mix\r\n\r\nTraditional gomasio mixes only include salt and sesame seeds, but some blends also include sugar or seaweed.\r\n\r\nIt is a traditional Japanese condiment that has been used for centuries. It is sprinkled on food instead of table salt. Unlike in the West, the Japanese never had the tradition of sprinkling raw salt on food. Instead, they prepare spices for table use to enhance and balance the flavors and nutrients of the food.\r\n\r\nGomasio is the main spice of the macrobiotic diet. The taste of gomasio is mostly salty with subtle flavors of sesame seeds\r\n\r\nGomasio is a simple spice but still ensures to provide nutrients such as:\r\n\r\nRich in minerals: magnesium, zinc and iron. Mixtures containing seaweed will often provide additional magnesium, iron, calcium and vitamins B1, B6.\r\n\r\nContains a low percentage of sodium. Because Gomasio has less salt than regular table salt. This makes Gomasio a great condiment if you want to reduce the amount of salt in your diet.\r\n\r\nYou can add Gomasio to your diet to treat and prevent diseases such as:\r\n\r\nHigh Blood Pressure and Iodine Deficiency', 6, 'img441.png', 100),
