(452, 'Tin Binh Ceramic Fish Sauce 41N 500ml', '13.00', 'Tin fish sauce - pure rin fish sauce of the past in a ceramic pot. The history of fish sauce dates back to 300 years in the ancient fishing village of Phan Thiet with the forefather Tran Gia Hoa, who was granted the title of mandarin by King Nguyen. openly gave birth to the Vietnamese fish sauce profession. The fish sauce ceramics covered with lime, labeled with square labels, were transported by gourd boats from the Ca Ty River across the continent of Cochin China to the central and northern regions and accounted for the largest market share in Vietnam at that time. The ancients used to call this pure fish sauce Tin fish sauce.\r\n\r\nWith a 300-year-old recipe from the Ancient Fishing Village, today\'s famous Tin fish sauce is a thick rind fish sauce drawn directly from a wooden barrel, ripened slowly for 12 months with fresh big fat anchovies and pure salt. .', 6, 'img448.png', 100),
(453, 'Tin Fish Sauce Red Label Glass Bottle 40N 500ml', '10.00', 'Tin Fish Sauce with red label, natural 40N protein, 500ml glass bottle, pure traditional pure fish sauce, clean fish sauce from a wooden tent with special pure salted anchovies. No preservatives. Absolute passion fruit from fish 40gN/l Fish paste in a 500ml glass bottle. Pure rin fish sauce (preferably imported fish sauce) High quality imported white glass material and square wood stamp main label on ancient paper background, delicate round label attached with a delicate bottle neck, not only delicious but also beautiful .\r\n\r\nPure Red Longan Fish Sauce Protein 40N Natural\r\n\r\nTin Fish Sauce with red label, natural protein level 40N, 500ml glass bottle, pure traditional pure fish sauce, clean fish sauce from wooden tents, especially pure salted anchovies, no preservatives.\r\n\r\nIt is Rin Nguyen Tinh fish sauce (the first fish sauce) that combines fish meat pulled directly from a slow-cooked wooden tent with fresh fatty anchovies and pure, completely natural salt.\r\n\r\nAbsolute protein from fish 40gN/l in glass bottles for daily dipping or cooking.\r\n\r\nImported high-quality white glass and ancient paper labels tied with delicate bottle necks are not only delicious but also beautiful.\r\n\r\nInstructions for use: Use for daily family dishes.\r\n\r\nStorage Instructions: Store in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight. Close the lid tightly after use.', 6, 'img449.png', 100),
