(455, 'Lumlum Organic Soy Sauce 200ml', '4.00', 'Origin: Thailand\r\n\r\nCertified organic to EU, USDA/NOP, IFOAM and Canada standards Specifications: 200ml bottle Organic lumlum soy sauce is made from organic soybeans grown in Chiangmai, Thailand. Ingredients: soybeans, water, salt, brown rice and brown sugar.\r\n\r\nInstructions for use: used as a dipping sauce, seasoning seasoning for food ...\r\n\r\nLumlum Organic Soy Sauce 200ml certified organic to EU, USDA/NOP, IFOAM and Canadian standards\r\nSpecification: 200ml bottle\r\nLumlum Organic Soy Sauce is made from organic soybeans grown in Chiangmai, Thailand.\r\nIngredients: soybeans, water, salt, brown rice and brown sugar.\r\nInstructions for use: used as a dipping sauce, seasoning seasoning for food', 6, 'img451.png', 100),
(456, 'Wan Ja Shan Organic Soy Sauce 300ml', '6.00', 'The product is USDA certified organic, made in the USA. No preservatives, flavor enhancers, gluten or synthetic flavourings are used. Delicious taste, close to Asian people. It takes no time to prepare the sauce, all the spices are encapsulated in this wonderful dipping sauce.\r\n\r\nIngredients: Water, Soybean*, Wheat*, Salt, Sugar*, Food Alcohol*. (from organic farming)\r\n\r\nInstructions for use: Use directly or in food processing.\r\n\r\nStorage: Store in a cool, dry place, avoid direct sunlight. Store refrigerated after opening.\r\n\r\nTHSD: 4 years from date of manufacture\r\n\r\nNSX & HSD: see on product packaging\r\n\r\nNet weight: 300 ml/bottle\r\n\r\nOrigin: USA', 6, 'img452.png', 100),
(457, 'Wan Ja Shan Organic Soy Sauce (Soy Sauce Less Sodium)300ml', '6.00', 'With the feature that the sodium content is 25% less than normal soy sauce, the product \"Less Sodium\" is considered a suitable choice for those who need to limit salt in their diets. body every day.\r\n\r\nWan Ja Shan low salt soy sauce:\r\n\r\n- Certified organic by the United States USDA, absolutely no genetically modified ingredients (GMOs)\r\n\r\n- Ensure the delicious taste, close to the Asian taste. Suitable for vegetarians.\r\n\r\n- No preservatives, no artificial colors, no MSG.\r\n\r\n- Does not contain harmful Alcohol, does not use the method of hydrogenation to generate trans-fat (bad fat) - Suitable for making marinades or dipping with meat, seafood, Dim-sum...', 6, 'img453.png', 100),
(458, 'Global Organics Low Salt Tamari Soy Sauce 250ml', '10.00', 'Origin: Packed in Australia with materials imported from the US.\r\nGlobal Organics soy sauce products do not add synthetic chemicals, pesticides or genetically modified ingredients to your body.\r\n\r\nProducts without the intervention of chemicals, organically grown foods only provide nutrients and are completely pure, great taste.\r\nGlobal Organics Low Sodium Soy Sauce:\r\n- Gluten-free\r\n- Not genetically modified\r\n- No milk, dairy products\r\n– Vegan\r\n– No nuts\r\nIngredients: water, soybeans*, salt, vinegar*, alcohol*.\r\n*Certified organic ingredients. Contains soy.*\r\nReduced sodium compared to regular soy sauces\r\n\r\n**Storage: After opening, close the lid tightly and store in a cool place (15-30 C).', 6, 'img454.png', 100),
(459, 'Mommy Bliss Organic Vitamin C Immune Booster Syrup 90ml', '15.00', 'Element:\r\n\r\n– Vitamin C from Organic Amla Extract, Zinc from Zinc glycinate, Vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol), organic elderberry, organic inulin, organic Echinacea, organic agave syrup, water, citric acid.\r\nCapacity: 90ml.\r\n- USDA organic certification.\r\nOrigin: USA.\r\nExpiry date: 730 days.\r\nUsing:\r\n- For children from 1 to 12 years old - Shake well before use.\r\n- From 1-4 years old: 5ml/day\r\n- 4-12 years old: 10ml/day\r\n- Best product use after 3 months of opening', 6, 'img455.png', 100),
(460, 'Maple Syrup 250ml', '16.00', 'New Zealand\'s BioGro certified organic Non-GMO, no preservatives No impurities, harmful chemicals Imported from Malaysia Safe to use\r\n\r\nMaple Syrup Maple Syrup brand Radiant with 100% Organic ingredients is safe to use for your family.\r\n\r\nMaple Syrup has a mild sweetness that is why they are often used as a substitute for honey. Maple syrup is often used with pastries such as pancakes, crepes, waffles, toasts, etc. When used to serve, maple syrup will be sprinkled directly on the surface of the cake for people to enjoy.\r\n\r\nIn addition to its use as a side dish, maple syrup is also used to spread on the surface of baked goods or baked goods before placing in the oven. After baking, the maple syrup layer on the outside will form an extremely delicious coating and increase the attractiveness of the dish as well as the cake. Maple syrup is also used directly with oats or cereals, this combination also gives a quite delicious and attractive taste.', 6, 'img456.png', 100),
(461, 'Organic Agave Agave Syrup 360g', '8.00', 'Origin: Spain European organic certification\r\n\r\nOrigin: Spain\r\n\r\nEuropean organic certification\r\n\r\nAgave syrup is a type of honey from the agave plant. Agave is a sweetening plant with high fructose content and low glycemic index. Consumption of foods containing fructose lowers blood sugar significantly more than foods containing sucrose or glucose.\r\n\r\nYou can use agave syrup to sweeten plant-based milk, breakfast cereals, and pancakes.\r\n\r\nSweetening products are very safe for health', 6, 'img457.png', 100);
